title: fruit bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and margarine.
Mix well.
Add nuts and fruit mix.

title: michele swank's banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture.
Mix until well blended. Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: cinnamon pickle rings
directions: Mix lime and cold water.
Add cucumber rings.
Soak for 24 hours.
Drain and wash.
Soak again in cold water for 3 hours. Drain, then simmer 2 hours in vinegar, red food coloring and alum.
Drain.
Make syrup of last five ingredients.
Boil and pour over cucumber rings.
Let stand overnight.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries.
Mix with sugar and set aside overnight. Mix jello, boiling water and juices.
Let thicken.
Add cranberries, pineapple, orange, celery and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: polish spaghetti
directions: Brown onions and sauerkraut in oleo.
Mix all other ingredients in 3-quart casserole dish.
Add onions and sauerkraut. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: steak with peppers
directions: Roast beef pot roast, covered, for about 4 hours at 325°, until falling apart.
Shred with forks or hands while still warm. Add Kraft barbecue sauce.
Refrigerate overnight to marinate.
Do not float meat in sauce; use your own judgment on amount of sauce. Reheat and serve on rolls.

title: lentil nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in oil until soft.
Mix ingredients and place in large, greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle generously with sesame seed.
Baked for 30 minutes, covered with aluminum foil or a cookie sheets, and then for 10 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with cashew gravy or your favorite gravy.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in two 9-inch pans.
Put coconut in bowl and let thaw.
Mix sugar, water and coconut; bring to a boil. Set aside to partly cool. Prepare frosting mix as directed on package. Stack cake by putting
1 layer on plate.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Spoon coconut mixture on cake and let soak in. Cover with frosting mix.
Repeat with second layer, covering cake with frosting mix.
Sprinkle with thawed coconut on sides and top of cake.
Top with red cherry.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and put into a 9x13 casserole dish sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples and place on a square of aluminum foil.
Fill apple hole with raisins, brown sugar and dash of cinnamon.
Wrap foil around apple and bake on hot coals.

title: angel cornsticks
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, dry yeast, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda.
Beat eggs in buttermilk.
Add vegetable oil, then dry ingredients.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: ham and cheese omelet
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add water, salt and pepper, beat to blend. Preheat large skillet, then add butter.
Make sure sides and bottom of skillet are greased.
Pour eggs into skillet.
As omelet sets around edge, lift with spatula and tilt skillet so uncooked mixture spreads underneath.
Repeat until omelet is creamy and set.
Spread with ham and cheese filling, covering half of omelet, then loosen edge all around.
Fold over filling and roll from handle to opposite side, using two turners.
Loosen with spatula and roll out on platter.

title: france's nut cake(very old recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture. Add pecans.
Pour into prepared 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and remove.

title: lo-cal cheese ball
directions: With fork, mash together cheeses.
Add milk and dressing mix. Shape into ball.
Roll in parsley to cover.
Chill overnight. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound (flatten) chicken breasts to about 1/4-inch thickness. Fry in 1 tablespoon margarine until golden brown on both sides. Remove to other dish.
Place scallions, mushrooms and carrots in a frypan with chicken broth and 1/2 cup wine.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Place chicken in sauce with another 1/2 cup wine and simmer until chicken is done (10 minutes).
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cake with chocolate peanut butter icing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans with 1 3/4-inch sides.
Prepare cake according to package directions, beating in 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Divide batter between 2 pans.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 20 minutes.

title: mini pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Place biscuits in a greased 1 to 2-inch muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon meat mixture into biscuit lined cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with a piece of green pepper. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 48 mini pizza cups.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: Drain chicken, reserving broth.
Place lettuce in bottom of a large salad bowl.
Arrange peas on top of lettuce.
Combine reserved broth and next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Spread half of mixture evenly over peas.
Layer carrots, chicken, eggs, celery and onion (in that order).
Spread remaining sour cream mixture over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and chill overnight.
Sprinkle bacon on top of salad before serving.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: perfect apple pie filling
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix with apples.
Pour into pie crust.
Drop slices of oleo on top.
Cover with lattice crust or crumb topping.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°; 30 minutes at 350° or 375°.
Yield:
2 pies.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Add coconut, pecans or other fruit, if desired.

title: rich chocolate fudge cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on box.
While cake is still warm, poke holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand sweet milk over cake and jar of hot fudge or caramel topping.
When cake is cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonful onto boiling stew.
Reduce heat.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dumplings.

title: dietetic pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: indonesian beef sate
directions: ***You will need bamboo skewers.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer graham crackers; add 1/2 pudding mix.
Put on another layer of graham crackers and frost.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle salt over them; let stand 2 hours, drain and squeeze.
Mix sugar and vinegar together and heat until hot.
Pour over pickles and onions; add celery seed. Put in jars or plastic containers.
Will keep in refrigerator 1 year.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Boil water and pour over oats.
Allow to stand for 20 minutes. Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add oats alternately with dry ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, fruit and 1 cup nuts.
Spoon into 3 well-greased pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes and cool in pans 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and butter.
Beat until smooth. Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
When cool, frost and sprinkle with remaining nuts.

title: honey-mustard dressing(low-fat)
directions: In a small bowl, stir together low-fat yogurt, honey, mustard and pepper.
Cover and chill to store.
Makes about 1 cup or 16 (1 tablespoon) servings.

title: colorful squash salad
directions: Mix zucchini squash, salt and ice water together and refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl and cream until smooth.
Add a few drops of food coloring (your choice of color).
Add sugar gradually.
Add salt and chopped nuts.
Mix ingredients.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, pie filling, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Put the remaining in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle the cup of crumbs mixture on top.
Bake another 15 minutes at 350°.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Cook and cool hard-boiled eggs.
Coat each egg with flour, then cover each egg with 1/4 pound of the sausage meat, being sure there are no holes in the sausage coating.
Dip in bread crumbs. Heat oil in deep, heavy pan.
Fry each egg until sausage meat is cooked and browned.
Cool; cut in half and serve.
Fantastic!

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Add milk, vanilla and hot water last.
Beat 5 minutes by hand.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Check, then bake until done.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs together.
Blend in flour, cocoa, pecans and vanilla; pour into greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
While cake is hot, cover with Marshmallow Creme.

title: danish apple sliceslincoln, nebraska
directions: Mix flour, 1 Tbsp. sugar and salt.
Cut in oleo.
Put egg yolk in a measuring cup and add enough milk to make 2/3 c.; mix.
Add to first mixture.
Mix like pie crust.
Roll 1/2 dough for jelly roll pan.
Put dough in pan, cover with corn flakes, then spread apples over flakes.
Sprinkle with 1 1/4 c. sugar and cinnamon. Roll out top crust, place over apples and crinkle edges.
Beat egg white stiff and spread over top crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: phyllis' chicken and peas
directions: Brown chicken in oil, about 10 minutes.
Spread cans of cream of mushroom soup in
13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer cans of English peas over soup.
Top with chicken pieces, placing a bay leaf under each one.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (covered) until chicken is done and sauce is thick.

title: grandmoo's dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Can substitute more safflower oil for less olive oil, if desired.
Shake very well until yellow. Use over fresh salads!

title: vegetable medley quiche
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spoon into crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: white cream frosting
directions: Melt in saucepan the oleo.
Blend in flour, salt and milk. Boil, while stirring, for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread on cake.

title: mary bowden's deviled eggs
directions: Mix the vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper and egg yolks together. Add just enough mayonnaise to keep mixture from being crumbly.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Place cheese and tomatoes in microwave.
Cook until cheese is smooth.
Cook sausage until done.
Drain and and add cheese mixture.
Keep warm in crock pot and serve with chips.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cook pumpkin and drain well.
Mash pumpkin through strainer. Add all ingredients, except flavoring and mix well.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Makes 3 pies.

title: scripture cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water briskly for 5 minutes.
Cool and add baking soda.
Cream sugar and shortening (butter).
Add beaten eggs.
Add raisins and liquid.
Add dry ingredients and nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoon on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Put sauerkraut in bowl.
Add celery, carrot and onion.
In another bowl, mix vinegar, oil, celery seed, sugar, salt and pepper.
Blend well and pour over sauerkraut.
Cover container and chill in refrigerator.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Mix fruit into jello.
Pour 1/2 (2 1/2 cups) into mold.
Let set.
Put sour cream on set layer.
Cover with remaining jello that has been at room temperature.
Refrigerate.

title: fat-free carrot cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add pineapple and vanilla. Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices, which have already been mixed together.
Fold in carrots, raisins and Grape-Nuts. Pour into Bundt pan, sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool approximately 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Frost with non-fat cream cheese frosting.

title: berry yogurt delight
directions: Crush 1/4 cup of the berries.
Halve the remaining berries. Combine crushed berries with yogurt and sugar.
Spoon halved berries into dessert bowls.
Top with berry-yogurt mixture. Serves 4.

title: sausage in the pot
directions: Cut X's in sausage at 1-inch intervals.
Brown sausage, scored side down, in oil in kettle, turning often.
Add to kettle the potatoes, carrots, turnips, celery and onions.
Add water.
Add parsley sprigs, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until vegetables are tender.
Remove sausage to center of serving platter; arrange vegetables around sausage.
Serve with a loaf of crusty bread.
Serves 6.

title: sauteed parsley
directions: Remove the heavy main stems from parsley, but leave tiny branch stems attached to the leaves.
Stir broth into melted butter, then add parsley and stir to coat.
Cover and cook over medium to medium-low heat (4 to 5 minutes).
Take care not to cook too long or parsley will become wilted.
Serve.

title: madge's meltaways
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into small paper cups or drop as cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool a full 10 minutes, especially as cookies on baking sheet.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in pan. Cook and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add oatmeal and vanilla. Drop on wax paper.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs and blend in butter, flour, sugar and milk.
Stir in cracker crumbs and corn.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° about 1 hour or until firm.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water and milk to a rolling boil. Remove from the heat. Add contents of both envelopes from the potato package. Let stand for 1 minute; whip with a fork. Place the cream cheese in a microwave-safe bowl; cover and heat at 70% power for 45 seconds or until softened. Stir into potatoes. Transfer into a greased 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Broil in oven for approximately 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: banana oat bran blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tin or use paper cups. Rinse blueberries with cold water.
Drain.

title: alyssa's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Place casserole into 13 x 9-inch pan. Fill pan with enough water to come halfway up side of casserole. Put pan with casserole on middle shelf of oven.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, carrot and green pepper.
Mix with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Set aside.
Cool remaining ingredients and put on cabbage mixture.

title: beefy mushroom cube steak
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle both sides of beef with soup mix.
Wrap in foil, sealing edges airtight with double fold. Place in oven for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli.
Mix
other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and
bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cracker crumbs to top.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: watermelon dessert
directions: Chill deep Tupperware bowl.
Pack lime sherbet around edge of bowl, center hollow.
Set in freezer until solid; pack in pineapple sherbet; set until frozen, put in 1/2 of raspberry sherbet. Sprinkle in chips; finish filling with raspberry sherbet.
Freeze until solid.
Unmold and slice like watermelon.

title: blueberry and banana pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add 1 cup sugar and the cream cheese.
Blend well.
Line crusts with bananas.
Top with Dream Whip mixture.
Spoon pie filling over mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: papa's lo-cal beans
directions: Place beans in covered 3 to 4-quart pot and cover with 3 inches of water.
Cook on very low heat for 3 hours.
Drain and fill with fresh water 2 to 3 inches above beans.
Add oil, bouillon cubes and Sweet 'N Low.
Bring it to low boil and cook until tender (about 4 hours).
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve with cornbread.
Open a window while cooking; window should remain open several days!

title: hot beef dip
directions: Mix together cheeses and fold in onion, pepper and beef.
Pat in pie plate and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot on crackers.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef with salt in deep kettle.
Add garlic and pepper.
Simmer slowly for 10 minutes, uncovered.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts and orange rind. Combine egg, milk and butter, add to flour mixture.
Fold in cranberries.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until hot.
Pour over miniature marshmallows.
Add whipping cream; beat until stiff.
Cut grapes in half, seed and drain.
Fold in your fruits and let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble and reserve about 2 tablespoons dripping.
Warm a salad bowl and place the lettuce, onion and bacon in the bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Toss well.
Add vinegar and sugar to the bacon drippings in frying pan. Bring to a boil and while hot, pour over the lettuce and toss well.
Serve immediately.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a cup of water dissolve 2 packages of dry yeast plus 1 tablespoon of sugar; let dry yeast work until it doubles.
Mix well and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours before you start pinching off the amount you want to cook.
Keeps very good for 2 weeks.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.
Cool. Frost with the following:

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese; finely chop pimentos.
Add mayonnaise and red pepper.
Blend all together.
This can be used as a dip for crackers or on bread for sandwiches.

title: senator gramm's award winning chili
directions: Brown the meat and onion and drain, if necessary. Add the tomato sauce, water, chili powder, salt, paprika, ground cumin, red pepper, garlic and 2 to 3 tablespoons flour.
Cook 1 to 2 hours.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons flour.
Cook 15 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash.
Layer with onions and bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rouladen(german recipe)
directions: Salt and pepper each slice of beef and spread with mustard. Put a slice of bacon on the slice of beef and add some onions and garlic and a the dill pickle.
Starting at the narrow end of the steak, roll jelly roll fashion and secure with toothpicks.

title: creole strip steak
directions: Put steak, salt, pepper, onions, celery, tomato juice and Worcestershire sauce in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6-8 hours. Turn to high.
Add green peppers, okra and mushrooms.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: potato souffle with onions
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into wedges.
Place in a saucepan.
Barely cover with boiling water.
Add dash of salt.
Simmer potatoes, uncovered, until just tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Mash potatoes.
Place in saucepan again.
Heat.
Add hot milk, butter, green onions, garlic and nutmeg.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Using long strokes, gently fold egg whites into mashed potatoes.
Pile mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/4-quart souffle dish.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until puffy and slightly golden on top.
Garnish with red pepper strips, if used. Serve immediately.

title: bake beans
directions: Empty cans in baking pan; add catsup, mustard and honey; stir well.
Dice onion; put in baking pan.
Add honey and stir.
Place bacon on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add carrots, cherries and juice.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder and add. Add nuts and egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Combine bread, ham and cheese cubes and spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs, mustard, milk and melted butter and pour over first mixture.
Top with remaining cup of croutons.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudgemellow candy
directions: In microwave, melt chocolate and peanut butter on Medium 2 to 3 minutes. Stir after each minute.
Fold in marshmallows and raisins.
Pour into square pan.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: caribbean baked crab
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and add 1 cup grated sharp cheese.
Put in baking dish.
Top with small amount of bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Put lid on and remove the lid the last 10 minutes.

title: a different pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Mix flour and sugar.
Then add milk and the eggs.
Beat well and stir in the vinegar, vanilla and butter. Add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Place in a cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
This makes a big pie.
The recipe can be doubled and made into 3 smaller size pies.
They freeze well.

title: banana-pineapple nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Combine dry ingredients. Stir in nuts. Combine rest of ingredients.
Add to dry mixture and stir until moistened. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mammaws tea
directions: Bring water to a boil, add tea bags.
Turn off fire and put cover on pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup sugar and enough water to make 2 quarts.

title: rotini salad
directions: Mix salad ingredients all together.
Mix the dressing ingredients together and pour over the rest.
Mix all together. Make this salad several days before serving so that the flavors blend.
This recipe makes a lot.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Crush cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread softened ice cream on top.
Pour fudge sauce on top of ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with nuts, cherries and cookie crumbs.
Serves 10.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook vermicelli. Reserve in cold water.
Add all ingredients and mix well!
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with Parmesan cheese.

title: raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour
two
9-inch
pans.
Mix flour, sugar, mayonnaise, milk,
eggs,
baking
soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves together
for two minutes.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake at
for 45 minutes.
Fill and frost with two cups whipped cream.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles
directions: Soak clean sliced cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamelware for 12 hours or overnight.
Remove sliced cucumbers from lime water.
Discard lime water.
Rinse 3 times in fresh cold water.
Soak 3 hours in fresh ice water.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and mixed pickling spices in a large pan. Bring to a low boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Remove syrup from heat and add sliced cucumbers.
Soak 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Boil slices in syrup 35 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars with hot slices.
Pour hot syrup over the slices, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cap each jar when filled.
Process pints 10 minutes, quarts 15 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice and soak in salt and water for 3 hours.
Slice onions; let stand 1 hour with cukes.
Drain good.
Bring to boil with other ingredients.
Let boil about 5 minutes.
Put in hot sterilized jars.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, cocoa and melted margarine in a bowl.
Add beaten eggs, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 35 minutes or until knife inserted in filling comes out clean or pie is firm when tapped with back of spoon.

title: lime-cucumber salad mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Pour into 1 large or 6 small molds and chill until firm.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain off liquid.
Place in casserole dish. Layer diced chicken over broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Spread bread crumbs over mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until all is hot clear through.
If prepared beforehand, place in refrigerator and then reheat before serving.

title: sweet sausage and potato soup
directions: Brown sausage, onions and bacon. Remove bacon and crumble it. Add chicken broth, water and potatoes. Simmer 15 minutes. Add crumbled bacon, sausage, kale and cream. Simmer 4 minutes and serve.

title: broccoli and wild rice bake
directions: Cook broccoli stem pieces, covered, in boiling salted water to cover about 5 minutes.
Add broccoli flowerets and cook 4 to 5 minutes more or until tender.
Drain.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of 8 x 8 x 3-inch pan.
Mix taco seasonings into sour cream until well blended.
Spread over refried beans.
Evenly sprinkle shredded cheese over sour cream mixture.
Evenly spread chopped olives, onions and tomatoes over cheese.
Serve with Tostitos corn chips.

title: delicious fried chicken
directions: Dip each piece of chicken in a mixture of the eggs and milk. Mix dry ingredients together.
After dipping chicken in the egg/milk mixture, coat each piece with flour mixture.
Fry in hot Crisco until brown on each side.
Then place on pan and put in 350° oven until good and tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: super moist lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except lemonade and 10x sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a tube pan sprayed with Pam.
Place warm cake in Pyrex pie plate and vent with knife.
Mix lemonade and 10x sugar and pour over cake.
Cake will soak up icing.

title: coconut nut cake topping
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Divide mixture between 2 baked 8-inch round cake layers.
Spread evenly on top of each cake layer.
Place cake dish on tray shelf in center position.
(Use ovenproof glass or ceramic dish that will withstand the browning element heat.)
Do one layer at a time, positioning the cake correctly under the browning element.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Dice ham and onions; saute in large cooking pot on medium heat until onion is clear and slightly brown.
Add water, tomatoes, potatoes, cabbage and rice.
Cook about 1/2 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Pat mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle small bag of chocolate chips over the top.
When they get soft, spread in marble fashion.
Then over this, spread the last 3 ingredients.

title: tin roof pie
directions: Put in 9-inch round pie dish the cereal, syrup and peanut butter.
Press firmly to make crust.
Then add vanilla ice cream to fill.
Sprinkle with crushed salted peanuts.
Freeze.
Let set out a few minutes before serving.
Top with chocolate syrup, if desired.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cornmeal, then add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat one minute or until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat and taco seasoning in skillet according to directions on package.
Add beans and warm thoroughly.
Chop lettuce and tomato and place in a very large bowl.
Add sliced onion.
Crush chips
slightly and add to lettuce mixture.
Pour warm meat mixture into salad bowl.
Toss with dressing. Top with cheese.
Additional chips may be served.
Drain fat from meat and from beans.

title: cherry winks
directions: Mix altogether and drop by spoon.
Put 1/2 cherry on top or can use a pecan, too.
Bake at 325°.

title: creamed baked corn
directions: Butter baking dish.
Mix ingredients together and place in dish.
Bake dish in a pan of water for 1 hour at 350°.
Check for doneness.

title: pecan-streusel coffee cake
directions: Stir together pecans, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon; set aside.

title: fresh peach crumb pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix with peaches.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Fill with peach mixture.

title: quick hamburger steaks
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, salt and pepper together.
Shape in oblong patties.
Brown well on both sides in a little shortening. Drain, if you desire.
Then pour one or two cans mushroom soup over beef patties.
Put in oven and bake approximately 30 to 60 minutes at 350° until soup taste is all through meat.
This is good to serve with rice or potatoes.

title: punch
directions: Mix equal parts of black cherry soda, cranberry juice and orange juice.
Add ice and serve.

title: taco pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on pizza pan.
Poke with a fork.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce. Simmer.
Bake crescent rolls for 8 to 10 minutes until brown. Spread hamburger mixture over crescent rolls.
Slice Velveeta cheese and add to top of hamburger.
Let melt in oven.
Watch closely.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, black olives and sour cream.

title: barbara's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 24 squares.

title: bagels
directions: In a mixing
bowl,
combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast. Combine water,
3 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Pour over flour mixture.
Beat
with
electric
mixer
on
low for 30 seconds, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in as much remaining flour as you can mix with a spoon.

title: marinated oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil, dip mix and dill weed in jar and shake well.
Put crackers on cookie sheet.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Stir until liquid is gone.
Let set awhile.
Store in airtight container.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Make dough as for biscuit dough.
Roll thin like pie crust. Dot with butter.
Cover with sugar.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Roll up as for jelly roll.
Cut in 2-inch sections. Lay each section touching in casserole dish.
Cover with milk. Sprinkle again with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in 400° oven until brown and bubbly.
Serve warm as a dessert.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Reserve 1 cup of the chicken broth. Combine soups, chilies, spices and chicken broth; blend well.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saut boned chicken breasts in 1 tablespoon oil. Stir in all the rest of the ingredients (except green peppers). Simmer about 20 to 30 minutes; add peppers and cook about 10 minutes more. Thicken with flour and water, if needed.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add green beans and tomato sauce.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven brown chicken - italian style(origin: italian)
directions: Wash chicken parts.
Coat with oil.
Season to taste and bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.
After 1/2 hour, turn and continue baking.

title: refrigerator potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes; add remaining ingredients.
Beat lightly and cool.
Pour ingredients into buttered dish.
Store in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: carolyn's barbecue beef brisket
directions: Place brisket into large deep pan.
On top place onions and pour barbecue sauce on top.
Cover with foil and place into preheated oven at 250° for 5 hours.
Serve with angel hair pasta and French bread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce and pecans.
Congeal.

title: cranberry nut bread(from polish family friend hedda)
directions: Sift together the first five ingredients.
Cut in oleo. Combine orange juice, orange rind and beaten egg; pour into dry ingredients to dampen.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased and floured pan.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Heat
oven
to
Beat
granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons butter,
the
egg
and
milk
in a large mixer bowl on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Spread batter in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
Place in 5-quart Pyrex bowl.
Add rice, Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup, chicken broth and seasonings.
Saute onion in butter and add to mixture. Take chicken meat off bones and tear or chop in bite-size pieces. Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 8.

title: crunchy peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar, Karo syrup and water together very, very slowly until it reaches 300 degrees. Spread 4 cups Jiffy peanut butter in a large pan.
Pour syrup over peanut butter and stir with wooden spoons as fast as possible.
Work up into a ball - pull out until it looks like a rope and cut with scissors.
Work with half a ball at a time.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Brown meat and onions, then drain grease.
Then add the rest of the ingredients over medium heat.
Serve with Fritos chips.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix together.
Put sliced
or strips of American cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1
hour
or at 20 minutes on High in microwave.

title: "green" salad
directions: In a bowl, mix lime Jell-O with boiling water. Stir until dissolved. Add pineapple and cool. In a blender, mix milk, mayonnaise, cottage cheese and horseradish. Blend very little. Add cooled Jell-O mixture and blend slightly. Add nuts to mixture. Pour in mold or pan and place in refrigerator to set.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain excess grease.
Stir in seasonings.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup and rice; mix well. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese slices. Replace top and simmer another 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Pour Jell-O into boiling water.
Let cool.
Crush bananas, thawed berries and chopped pecans.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into a pan and chill.
Spread sour cream and then top with remainder of Jell-O.
Top with Cool Whip after chilling.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine other ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring until moist.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger meat stew
directions: Brown meat.
Drain grease off.
Put in large saucepan and add all the other ingredients.
Simmer long enough to soften the noodles.

title: homemade orange-pineapple sherbet
directions: Pour pineapple and milk into 4-quart ice cream freezer.
Fill to fill line with Orange Crush.
Freeze in churn as you would ice cream.

title: pasta with tomatoes and prosciutto
directions: Saute onions in oil and butter.
Add Prosciutto and cook for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add to cooked pasta.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out sugar dough mix in pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, milk and 1/2 cup sugar; spread onto cooled dough.
Slice fruit and spread on top of pizza.
Mix together orange juice, lemon juice, cornstarch and 1/4 cup sugar. Bring to a boil and stir over medium heat until thick.
Let cool and spread on top of fruit.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix together and chill until firm.

title: baked chicken
directions: Lay chicken breasts or pieces of chicken over the mixture. Sprinkle with 1 package of dry onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Defrost vegetables slightly.
Add vegetables and juice and season to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour, adding water, if needed.
Excellent reheated.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Make jello. Add strawberries. When this starts to gel, fold in the Cool Whip. Break angel food cake into a large bowl.
Using a wooden spoon, gently fold Cool Whip mixture into the cake pieces. Pour into serving dish. Garnish as desired. Chill.

title: turkey and rice dressing
directions: Put the red peppers in the turkey.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until the mixture boils.
Cool and pour over two pints fresh strawberries arranged in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate or shallow ovenproof dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: my moma's best meat loaf
directions: Mash meat in a bowl; put in egg and crumbled crackers.
Add 1/2 bottle of Heinz 57 sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix together with spoon.
Spread in bowl or casserole dish.
Pour remaining 57 sauce on top; spread across the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: special day dessert
directions: Whip the cream.
Beat together sugar, vanilla and cream cheese; fold in whipped cream and pineapple.
Line the sides and bottom of a 9-inch pan with ladyfingers.
Chill several hours. Spread pie filling over top.
Yields 10 servings.

title: curried baked chicken breasts(serves 4)
directions: Wash chicken breasts and dry carefully; rub with lemon.
Heat oil in large frying pan over moderate heat.
Add chicken and brown lightly on all sides.
Remove to 2-quart baking dish.
Cook onion 1 minute in pan; stir in flour, salt and curry powder; add chicken broth, milk and Kitchen Bouquet.
Stir constantly until sauce thickens and boils.
Pour sauce over chicken and cover dish.
Bake at 350° until chicken is tender (about 45 minutes).

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in an unbaked pie shell at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Stir corn, salt, pepper and flour in with well beaten egg yolks.
Fold in 3 egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Fry in salad oil until brown on both sides.

title: huckleberry parfait
directions: Recipe may be doubled.

title: pork chops and onion
directions: Brown chops.
Spread the uncooked rice in bottom of baking dish.
Reserve 1 tablespoon seasonings from onion soup mix. Sprinkle rest over rice.
Drain mushrooms; reserve liquid.
Pour mushrooms over rice.
Add hot water to reserved liquid to make 2 cups; pour over rice.
Arrange browned chops on top; sprinkle with reserved soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil; cook 10 minutes longer, until liquid evaporates.

title: turtle cake
directions: *If cake mix does not call for oil, use 3/4 cup margarine instead of 1/4 cup.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed on box.
Rinse in cool water in colander.
Toss in remaining ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: party beef stick
directions: Put beef bites into crock-pot.
Mix mustard and jelly in separate bowl.
Pour into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 20 minutes.
Switch to lowest setting and continue cooking for two hours.
Stir periodically to keep from sticking.

title: english peas-cheese casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in medium-size casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Combine chicken, white sauce, egg yolk, lemon juice and seasonings.
Cool. Form in cones, cylinders or balls.
Roll in crumbs. Dip in egg, diluted with water. Roll in crumbs again. Fry in deep fat at 385° about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel. Serves 8.

title: mint cooler
directions: Cook sugar and water for 5 minutes. Add other ingredients. Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Strain and store in refrigerator. When serving, add ginger ale or Tom Collins mix. Serve over ice. Makes 6 to 8 glasses.

title: granny's fast peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, milk, sugar and salt.
Add to melted oleo.
Add canned peaches. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven
to
Melt
margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Chop
frozen broccoli in food processor.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan with melted margarine.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Place chicken in pan and put slices of cheese on top.
Combine soup and wine or juice.
Add to chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing over all.
Drizzle 1/4 cup melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan. Saute onions and pork for a few minutes. Add rice and thin soy sauce.
Mix well.
In the middle, add eggs.
Toss together until eggs are done.

title: microwave broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1-quart covered casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Add onion; stir gently.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add soup; stir gently.
Cover and cook 3 minutes. Add cheese and rice.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake in ovenproof bowl 20 minutes at 350° to 400°.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: roma bella tortellini boscaiola
directions: In large frying pan over medium heat, heat olive oil.
Remove the sausage meat from the casing and cook it in the pan, breaking it up into small pieces with the back of a spoon.
Add peas, mushrooms and wine and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cream to the pan; bring to a very gentle boil and let simmer for about 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until the sauce reduces and thickens slightly.
In a large pot of salted boiling water, cook the tortellini for 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain and add the tortellini to the sauce and stir for a minute to mix thoroughly and heat through.
Serves 2.

title: milky way cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Melt candy bars and butter, stirring frequently in large, heavy Dutch oven over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar. Combine egg yolks, buttermilk and baking soda in a small bowl until blended.
Combine flour and salt in another bowl, add to candy mixture alternately with ingredients.
Stir in pecans.

title: hot apricots
directions: Drain apricots and place in baking dish, turned up.
Sprinkle a mixture of crushed Ritz crackers and brown sugar.
Melt oleo and pour over apricots.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together well shortening, sugars and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Place remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Pour sauce over vegetables.
Stir gently to mix.
Cover and chill for several hours before serving.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, stirring in between.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts; blend until mixed.
Bake at 350° in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: rosa marina(fruit macaroni salad)
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, then drain.
Drain juice from pineapple and oranges and save juice.
Cook juice, 3/4 c. sugar, flour and eggs until thick.
Pour over macaroni.
Let refrigerate overnight.
Add Cool Whip, cherries (cut up), oranges and pineapple (cut up).
Refrigerate until cold.
Tastes just like a fruit salad.

title: chewy bars
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut while hot.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve cold.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Beat egg with fork to combine.
Sprinkle Italian flavored bread crumbs on a sheet of waxed paper. Dip chicken breasts into egg, then crumbs, turning until it is completely coated.
In a large skillet, heat the oil with the garlic over medium-medium high heat. Add chicken and saute 4 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Pour spaghetti sauce around chicken. Top each piece of chicken with a slice of cheese. Simmer, covered, 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine all ingredients but cheese and ham.
On wax paper or foil, pat meat into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham on top and then sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting from the short end, roll up meat (using the paper to lift).
Seal ends and edges.
Place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Place cheese wedges on top and return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.
Pour over washed and dried cukes packed in quart jars.
(Place one stalk dill at bottom of jar and one on top.)

title: christmas cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add frozen juice.
Put into punch bowl.
Add cold water.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: almond poppy seed dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix for 30 seconds.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar gradually, then add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Stir well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake 35 minutes longer.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still warm, pierce with fork and pour condensed milk mixed with pina colada mix over cake.
Let cool and ice with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut and refrigerate.

title: fluffy corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Beat
eggs
well and add to milk. Add to dry mixture.
Add corn.
Spray 2-quart casserole with Pam. Pour in mixture and
bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir from bottom several times during
first
hour and then do not stir again.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter or olive oil until tender.
Add the next 9 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 25 minutes.
Add shrimp and parsley.
Simmer, uncovered, until shrimp are cooked, about 10 minutes.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers; add other ingredients.
Add milk last.
Mix well.
Pack into tube pan lined with wax paper.
Chill.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, combine all ingredients until evenly coated. Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: hot relish
directions: Grind all ingredients and add as much of the pepper juice as you desire.
Put in pot and cook about 10 minutes.
Add green food coloring.
Put in jars and seal.

title: strawberry cake dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; stir in strawberry mixture until slightly jelled.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Cook sausage.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Mix eggs, milk and cheese together.
Tear bread and add.
Add sausage. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: herb biscuits
directions: In small baking pan melt the oleo and sprinkle with all other ingredients.
Press Hungry Jack biscuits onto mixture, turning over so both sides are coated.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Very good with Italian food or stew.

title: low-fat french fried potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, either peeled or not, for 10 minutes; drain. Let cool.
Cut into strips.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
Place potatoes on sheet so they're not touching.
Spray potatoes with vegetable spray and sprinkle seasoned salt over them.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for chipped ham
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat, stirring occasionally.

title: hot spinach-cheese dip
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain thoroughly, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Add reserved spinach liquid, milk and next 6 ingredients, stirring until cheese melts.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine breadcrumbs and 1 teaspoon butter; sprinkle over spinach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Serve hot with crackers or vegetables.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together oleo, Crisco, sugar and egg yolks.
Combine flour, soda and salt and add alternately with buttermilk.
Beat egg whites and fold in. This makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix vanilla, bananas, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in butter, cereal and flour mixture.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Can also be baked in muffin pan for muffins.

title: hungarian-style chicken noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions for 4 minutes; drain.
In a large bowl, stir together remaining ingredients except 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Stir in hot noodles; spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: "philly" miracle whip wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Place drinking glass in center of serving platter.
Dip rounded tablespoonfuls of mixture to form ring around glass; smooth with spatula.
Remove glass.
Garnish with chipped parsley and pimento just before serving, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: green beans and potatoes
directions: Break beans into bite size and boil until tender; drain.
Boil potatoes whole until tender; drain and cut into chunks.
Cool slightly.
Add olives and stir.
Mix all other spices and oil in a separate bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes, then stir into beans and potatoes.
Mix thoroughly; let sit a few more minutes.
If you want, you can garnish with a few small pieces of pimento or red bell pepper.

title: hidden treasure strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and pour in fruit and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13 pan.
Chill until firm.
Store other mixture at room temperature.
Prepare cheesecake according to package directions.
Spoon over chilled filling.
Top with remaining jello mixture and chill.

title: pasta salad *
directions: Cook pasta; drain and put in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Toss and serve.
It's also terrific the next day!

title: basic vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla and evaporated milk.
Pour in mixer can.
Fill to fill line or 2/3 full with homogenized milk.

title: festive franks
directions: Saute hog dogs, onion and green pepper in margarine until onion is soft.
Cook macaroni in boiling water.
Drain.
Add to hot dog mixture.
Stir in milk, salt and thyme.
Stir in tomato sauce and 2 1/2 cups of cheese.
Pour into 4-quart ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: pork with sweet potatoes
directions: Sprinkle pork roast with lemon pepper.
Sprinkle pork roast with 1 Tbsp. flour.
Dust a large oven bag with additional flour. Cut six 1/2 in. slits in bag.
Roast at 375 degrees for 1 hour. Combine honey, lemon juice, and brown sugar.
(Put juice into pan from bag.)
Place sweet potatoes around roast.
Spoon mix over roast and potatoes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cover and roast to 1 - 1 1/4 hour until tender.
Arrange apples, cut side up, on top of potatoes.
Cut slit in orange slices and twist, arrange around roast.
Cook until tender for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 11 x 2 pan with Pam or other nonstick spray.
Mix applesauce, sugar, egg whites and vanilla. Mix in flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in apples and nuts. Spread in pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place paper liner in muffin pan or grease.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Sift in large bowl.
Stir in bananas, milk, oil, egg and nuts.
Stir until batter is moist.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Bake for about 20 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash and cut up peppers, discarding all insides.
Grind the peppers and onions together and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes
and drain in colander until dry.

title: camp stew
directions: Cook all meat together.
A pressure cooker may be used.
Cook until meat is tender and falls apart; cool.
Take out bones; set aside, retaining all broth.
Chop potatoes and onions into 1-inch cubes.
Cook potatoes, onions and whole kernel corn together until tender in large boiler, using enough water to cover contents and prevent scorching.
Add boned meat and 2 quarts broth from meat into Irish potatoes, onions and corn.
A large canner or large pressure cooker bottom will be needed to cook contents.
Add all seasonings.
Cook on low for 2 hours.
Thicken with 6 slices of bread, if needed.
Makes about 10 to 12 quarts.
Stir this mixture often while cooking to prevent scorching.

title: homemade butterfinger brickle ice cream
directions: The following ingredients are based on a one-gallon freezer:

title: banana fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Stir about 1 cup banana chunks into batter.
Heat 2 to 3 inches of oil in a deep fat fryer.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil and fry until done, about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll in powdered sugar glaze.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: With electric mixer, cream shortening.
Add sugar and egg and beat well.
In separate bowl, mix together flour, spices, salt and baking soda.
Stir flour mixture into creamed shortening mixture.
Mix in persimmon pulp, raisins and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls, 2-inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Bring water, salt and butter to a boil.
Add rice; set aside. Thaw broccoli.
In large mixing bowl combine broccoli, soup, milk, rice and Cheez Whiz.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into an electric ice cream freezer container.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Store leftovers in freezer.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook, drain and squeeze water out of spinach.
Add other ingredients and mix; chill.
Form balls tablespoon size.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chewy charlies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter, raisins and vanilla. Cool and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all
together with the exception of cracker crumbs. Put into
buttered
casserole
dish.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Remove chicken from bone and save broth (3 cups). Combine all remaining ingredients together with chicken and broth. Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: "dirt"
directions: Crush Oreos fine.
Whip butter and cream cheese.
Whip pudding with milk until thick.
Add pudding with cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Start with layer of cookies in the bottom of pail or dish; then a layer of pudding mixture; continue to layer.
Finish top with cookies.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Clean chicken; cook in slow cooker 6 hours.
Debone chicken and set aside.
Use 3 to 4 cups of broth; add chopped celery and hard-boiled eggs (chopped), then add cream of chicken and simmer until done.
Roll biscuits out and place on bottom of pan.
Spread chicken; add broth mix.
Roll rest of biscuits and lay on top of chicken.
Bake at 375° until bread is a light brown.

title: louise's chili
directions: Brown
ground
beef.
Cook onion over low heat in skillet; add to meat.
Simmer with seasonings 10 minutes.
Add all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: zucchini yeast bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Beat in milk, sugar, butter, orange peel and salt; mix well. Add the zucchini, raisins, whole-wheat flour, cardamom and enough all-purpose flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/4 hours. Punch dough down. Shape into a loaf. Place in greased 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan to cool on a wire rack.

title: fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour buttermilk into shallow bowl; add chicken and turn to coat.
On paper plate combine cornflake crumbs and sesame seed.
Dredge chicken in crumbs/seed mixture.
Arrange chicken
on nonstick baking sheet until chicken is brown and crispy, about 40 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in heavy pan.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients and salt to taste.
Simmer 20 minutes. Serve on toasted hamburger buns with sliced hamburger pickles. Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: chili cheese rice quiche
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Combine eggs, milk, garlic salt and pepper.
Stir in rice, Mozzarella cheese, onion, pimento and jalapeno peppers.
Spoon into an 8-inch pie plate coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until inserted knife near center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chitterlings("chitlins")
directions: Place chitterlings in Dutch oven and add enough water to cover.
Add salt and red pepper and mix.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 1 hour or until fork-tender.
Drain well.
Mix together the eggs, flour and evaporated milk to make batter. Dip chitterlings in batter to coat and fry in hot oil in large skillet to brown, turning once.
Serve hot.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Cream all together until light and fluffy. Place in a graham cracker crust. Top with a can of cherry pie filling or other flavor.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Combine in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green beans (greek style)
directions: Wash and trim beans; cut in half.
Heat oil in large saucepan. Layer beans, onions, lemon juice, salt, pepper, bread crumbs and herbs (reserve 1/2 cup parsley for garnish).
Last layer should be beans.
Add water; cook over low heat for 30 to 35 minutes, until beans are tender.
Garnish with parsley; cool.
Serve cold as accompaniment to main dish.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: peanut butter delight squares
directions: Mix graham crackers, powdered sugar, peanut butter and margarine.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips or almond bark in double boiler or microwave.
Pour over other ingredients in pan.
Cool until set and cut into squares.

title: seasoned taco meat
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Add water and seasonings. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until water is absorbed. Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Fry pork or sausage; drain off fat.
Add ham, corned beef, onion, parsley and salt.
Fry until brown.
Stir in mustard, salt and flour.
Cook 10 minutes and cool.
Add kraut and 1 cup juice. Mold into bite size balls.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Makes about 100 balls. (They freeze well.)

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Cut into 1-inch pieces and cook until tender.
Melt butter; mix in flour and milk to make a smooth cream.
Pour over potatoes and stir gently until covered.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: onion pie supreme
directions: Heat oil in a wide frying pan over medium heat.
Add onions, nutmeg and salt; cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are very soft and lightly browned.
Remove from heat and let cool. Meanwhile, prepare tart shells, add onions to eggs, then divide mixture evenly between shells.
Trim off dough about 1/2-inch above filling.
On a floured board, roll out trimmings, cut them into 3/4-inch wide strips and weave strips over each tart to make a lattice topping.
Fill spaces between lattice with olive and pimiento slices.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until pastry is golden.
Let cool briefly before cutting into wedges to serve.
Makes 2 tarts.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook onion, garlic and butter over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 3 to 4 minutes. Add tarragon, lemon juice, hot sauce, steak sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Stir and cook 5 to 6 minutes, until shrimp turns pink.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Mix together popcorn and peanuts.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla. Pour over popcorn and peanuts until well coated.
Spread on shallow baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool on aluminum foil.
Store in airtight container.

title: cooked dressing for slaw
directions: Mix sugar, salt, mustard, flour, egg, milk and vinegar in top part of a double boiler, blending thoroughly after the addition of each ingredient.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes quite thick.
Add butter; blend thoroughly and cool.
Thin with cream or milk, if desired, when making the slaw.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and onions;
slice about 1/4 to 3/8-inch thick. Place
in	large
container.
Add whole garlic cloves; mix together.
Sprinkle salt over and mix.
Pour over 2 trays ice cubes;
let
stand	for 3 hours, adding more ice cubes if needed. Drain thoroughly.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices; bring
to boil.
Pour
over
well drained cucumbers.	Mix and ladle into jars;
store in refrigerator.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in sheet cake pan. While hot, poke holes in cake and pour caramel sauce over cake. Cool.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water and let set until bubbly.
Combine milk, sugar, salt, shortening, about 2 cups of the flour and eggs. Add bubbly yeast and beat well, then add remaining flour gradually.
Turn onto floured board and knead about 5 minutes. Let rise in greased bowl until double in bulk.
Divide into two portions.
Each will make a loaf of bread.
Roll each section into large rectangle; spread generously with margarine, cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up jelly roll fashion; tuck under ends and place in well-greased bread pan.
Let rise until triple in bulk; bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: salad with creamy dressing
directions: In a large bowl, toss salad greens, tomatoes and cucumbers. Set aside. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, Thousand Island dressing and milk. Mix well. If desired, stir in eggs. Serve over salad.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tight container. To serve, use 2 teaspoonfuls to a tea cup of boiling water.

title: one rise monkey bread
directions: Grease a 12-cup tube pan.
In large bowl, blend 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, water, butter and egg at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed; stir in remaining flour by hand.
Knead on floured board until smooth.
Press or roll dough to 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Using sharp knife, cut dough into diamond-shape pieces by cutting into 2-inch strips diagonally across dough.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in blender.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar in a bowl. In a large bowl mix milk and pudding, then add Cool Whip.
Mix cheese mixture in with pudding mixture. Refrigerate.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Fry onion and peppers in a small amount of oil.
Add meat, stirring until well mixed and meat is white.
Remove from heat and stir in Old English cheese.
Mix with other ingredients and place in large baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chow mein noodles.
Serves 8.

title: swedish pie(sweden)
directions: Beat egg until light.
Add sugar and beat.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and baking powder.
Beat well.
Fold in nuts and apples.

title: carrot casserole almondine
directions: Wash, trim and peel carrots.
Slice diagonally.
Drop into boiling salted water.
Return to boil and cook for 10 to 15 minutes until tender-crisp.
Drain and turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour tomatoes over, sprinkle with marjoram and thyme; mix.
Mix cracker crumbs with margarine and almonds.
Spread over top.
Cover and refrigerate until nearly serving time.
Uncover, place in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot through and crumbs lightly toasted.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Add molasses and salt in water.
Cool.
When lukewarm, add dissolved yeast and flour.
Mix or beat well.
Cover and let rise to double in bulk.
Beat again and place into greased bread pan, having pan half full.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Chop shrimp and fold in dip.
Use with your favorite crackers.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spoon potato mixture into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water; drain. Debone and break in large pieces. Mix all other ingredients except bread crumbs. Mix with chicken. Put in large casserole. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
May refrigerate overnight before baking.

title: pretzel salad(dessert)
directions: Mix
pretzels,
margarine
and
sugar
(3 tablespoons). Press into 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch pan and bake 8 minutes on 400°. Cool. Combine cream
cheese, 1 cup sugar and mix well.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip
and spread over pretzels.
Add 2 cups boiling water to jello
and
then add frozen strawberries.
Let jello mixture set for
minutes
then
pour
over
cream cheese. Refrigerate until set.

title: horseradish pickles
directions: Put cut pickles back into original jar and add remaining ingredients.
Shake well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: sally's asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk until smooth.
Arrange a layer with 1/2 of the ingredients in this order:
asparagus, peas, eggs, cheese, soup mixture, pimentos and cracker crumbs.
Make 2 layers. Reserve enough crumbs for top.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole(serves 4)
directions: Pour rice, butter and water in casserole dish.
Lay in chicken.
Pour soup over chicken.
Bake at 325° one hour.

title: parsonage punch
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; chill at least 2 hours.
Pour juice mixture in punch bowl.
Scoop ice cream in to mixture.
Add ginger ale.
Serve immediately.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer until well blended.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix all together and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not look at it once in the oven.
Bake in covered pan or casserole.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Dot 9 x 13-inch dish with butter.
Cover with raw rice. Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Lay chicken on top.	Mix soup and water.
Pour carefully over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add enough cracker crumbs to stiffen.
Shape into croquettes.
Dip croquettes into slightly beaten egg; roll in cracker crumbs and fry in hot oil until browned.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Stir until well mixed.
Do not beat.
Add pineapple and bananas. Do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a 350°oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Have very cool before icing.

title: caramel custard
directions: Place brown sugar in bottom of each custard cup.
Mix egg, salt, milk, sugar and vanilla and blend thoroughly.
Pour slowly into custard cups.
Place custard cup sin pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Serve in cups or turn upside-down on serving plate (caramel sauce will be on top).
Yields 4 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat oil and coat beef cubes in flour.
Brown meat.
Pour off excess oil.
Chop carrots, potatoes and celery.
Add tomatoes and all remaining ingredients except peas.
Add water just to cover. Add just enough Kitchen Bouquet to get the color you want.
Simmer slow 2 to 3 hours until vegetables are soft and gravy is thick. Now add peas and simmer until peas are cooked.

title: dressing for cole slaw
directions: Cook and stir until thick.
Combine with 4 cups shredded cabbage.

title: zucchini torta
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs, oil, onion, parsley and oregano. To this mixture, add Bisquick and combine thoroughly.
Add shredded zucchini and mix thoroughly.
Pour into baking pan.
The size of the pan determines the thickness of the torta.
The larger the pan, the thinner.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes or until it is done.

title: double corn dodgers
directions: Melt butter in a small skillet over moderate heat.
Add onion and saute until tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Preheat oven to 425°.
In a mixing bowl, stir together dry ingredients; stir in onion, corn, eggs and milk just until blended.
Drop the batter in heaping tablespoons 2 inches apart on well-greased baking sheet. Bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot, with butter.

title: pear pickles
directions: Peel, core and quarter pears.
Mix sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Add pears and spice.
Boil until pears are tender and fill jars.
Cover with syrup.
There must be sufficient liquid to cover.

title: scones
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth and light.

title: honey chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper, then cover with ketchup and honey.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, then at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: root beer float(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on low speed.
Add ice cubes.

title: chili pepper casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Lay peppers on bottom; sprinkle on cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put all ingredients, except corn and soda in saucepan and boil for 5 minutes or less.
Remove from heat, add soda and beat.
Mix cooked syrup mixture with corn, tossing to coat.
Spread corn in large roasting pan and bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
You may add nuts, if you like.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Let chill several hours and then roll in chopped pecans.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Cook together sugars and milk, stirring constantly, until firm and soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla. Add pecans and let cool.
Beat and drop on wax paper.
Use a candy thermometer for best results.

title: tomato relish
directions: Bring to boil in large pot the first 10 ingredients; boil 1/2 hour.
Add tomato paste.
Boil another 1/2 hour.
Pour into clean jars.
Can be frozen or canned.

title: easy broccoli salad
directions: Note: I usually double the broccoli, onions, bacon and raisins.

title: pasta salad with sundried tomatoes and pine nuts
directions: Toss all ingredients together gently one hour before serving. Yield:
8 to 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients until hot and pour over veggies.
Add Minute rice (uncooked).
Sprinkle with onion flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry breakfast bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Add milk and blueberries. Bake at 350° for about half an hour.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of waxed paper and pound out.
Blend cheese, crumbs, parsley, onions and 1/4 cup butter. Shape into 6 balls.
Season inside of each chicken breast with salt and pepper.
Place stuffing ball at one end of each breast.
Turn long sides of breast toward center just enough to make a neat fold. Roll up each breast as for a jellyroll.
Secure ends with skewers or toothpicks.
Brush rolls with oil and butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Arrange on medium-hot grill.
Cover and cook 15 minutes. Brush with oil and butter; turn and brush again.
Cover and continue cooking about 10 minutes more or until done.
Brush with oil and butter again just before serving.
Top with packaged mushroom sauce, if desired.

title: oven baked french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into thin fries.
In a large bowl, lightly beat egg with a fork until foamy.
Stir in chili powder and red pepper.
Add potatoes and toss to coat well.
On a nonstick cookie sheet, spread potatoes in a single layer.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine
corn starch, 1 1/4 c. sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind. Beat egg yolks, add to cream corn starch mixture. Gradually add boiling water. Heat to boiling over direct heat and then boil gently

4 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Gradually beat in the 6 Tbsp sugar. Spread meringue over top of pie, carefully sealing in all the filling by spreading meringue to touch all edges of crust. Bake in hot oven, 425° 4 to 5 minutes or until browned. Cool on a cake rack away from drafts. Serve cold. Makes 1
8 inch pie.

title: cajun black-eyed peas
directions: Cut onion into slices and add all the ingredients to peas. Slowly boil until onions are tender.
You may add more Cajun seasoning if you prefer spicier dish.

title: zucchini-banana-blueberry cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix in a separate bowl the next 4 ingredients.
Add to the sifted ingredients.
Next add the zucchini, blueberries and bananas.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean and bread is a medium brown. Let sit for 5 minutes before removing.

title: banana orange cake
directions: Combine ingredients. Put into greased and floured pan.	Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix oleo and flour; pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy ziti
directions: Saute diced onions, tomatoes and green peppers in a lightly greased skillet.
Add a little water to prevent burning.
Add ground meat, seasonings, sugar and vinegar.
When meat is cooked, add spaghetti sauce and simmer until mixture thickens over a low heat.
(You may want to increase seasoning depending on the taste.) While meat is cooking, cook ziti noodles (follow directions on box).
Grate the Mozzarella cheese.
Preheat oven at 325°.
In an 8 x 11-inch casserole dish place a layer of meat sauce, top with a layer of ziti, follow with a layer of grated Mozzarella cheese. Continue the layers, ending with meat sauce.
Cover with foil and bake for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese is cooked and bubbly.
Uncover and let brown for about 5 minutes.
Your ziti is ready.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg and pulp.
Add flour. Then spices, nuts and soda.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet; press with sugar on bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour macaroni in melted butter and stir well, until it coats macaroni.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Chunk cheese over top.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not cover or stir.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, peanuts and salt in 1-1/2 quart casserole. Cook 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and cook 1 minute.
Add soda, stir and quickly pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: frosted big apple pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg yolks slightly in a measuring cup with fork and blend in enough cold water to make a scant cupful.
Roll out like any pastry.
Makes pastry for 1 Frosted Big Apple Pie or 3 (2-crust) pies.

title: pudding sundaes
directions: Kids love to make and eat this.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend
potatoes
and
sugar
in mixer; add eggs, 1 at a time. Beat after each egg.
Add oleo, milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: ever ready muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a very large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store in a tightly covered container in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
Bake as needed in muffin tins at 400°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: curried butternut squash soup
directions: Melt butter; add onions and curry and cook, covered, over low heat for 25 minutes.
Peel, seed and chop squash and add to onion mixture with chicken stock and apples.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes.
With a potato masher, mash mixture until fine but not pureed.
Add apple juice.
Add more stock if needed and heat.
Serve garnished with shredded apple.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot sherbet
directions: Mix water and sugar and bring to a boil.
Let cool.
