Puree the apricots, using the syrup also.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in freezer and freeze until firm.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavoring and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Work together 1 cup flour, coconut, sugar and margarine for the crust.	Spread mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: If chicken is large, brown in hot fat or boil 15 minutes. Place in pan and sprinkle uncooked rice over chicken.
Pour soups and broth or water over this; cover with foil.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil last 15 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until barely tender.
Drain excess water.
Chop onion and cook with scrambled hamburger.
Drain excess fat.
Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts and remove bones.
Cut in cubes.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add cheese and melt.
Add soup, Ro-Tel and chicken.
Drain spaghetti. Mix well with cheese mixture.
Pour into greased oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mary's porcupines
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, raw rice, bell pepper, salt, pepper, chili powder and garlic powder.
Add raw eggs; mix and shape into medium-size meat balls.
Place meat balls in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce and water over meat balls.
Bake until rice puffs up and is tender.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: oriental fish and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, thoroughly blend Vegetable Recipe soup mix, cornstarch, ginger and garlic powder. Stir in water and soy sauce; set aside. In large skillet, heat oil and cook green onions and broccoli 1 minute or until broccoli is crisp-tender. Add soup mixture and fish.
Cook, stirring frequently, 3 minutes or until fish is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat with onion. Add all other ingredients except for Doritos and cheese.
Pour half of meat mixture into a long baking dish. Top with crushed Doritos.
Pour remainder of meat on top. Top with grated cheese and bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: *Can use 2 cups sugar.

title: snack stuff
directions: Mix all together and keep in airtight container.

title: potato casserole
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, onion, chopped bell pepper and parsley. Mix 1 can mushroom soup and milk. Add salt and pepper. Pour over potatoes. Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Mix the cocoa, flour and sugar.
Add melted butter, vanilla and eggs.
Bake in pie pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine eggs and milk in mixing bowl.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture and beat until smooth. Test to see if mixture flows through a funnel freely.
If too thick, add milk.
If too thin, add flour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute the shrimp in the butter or oil along with the garlic. Add the bell pepper.
Add the wine vinegar.
Cook for about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add the soup with the basil and oregano and simmer as you like, usually about 5 to 10 minutes.
Also add the water (or will be too thick).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup crumbs to sprinkle on top.

title: grannie's peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter; beat together sugar, vanilla, eggs and peanut butter.
In separate bowl combine flour, bran, oats and soda. Stir mixture into butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes or until done. Remove and cool.
Makes 5 to 7 dozen.

title: pure maple butternut fudge
directions: Heat syrup and cream slowly, continuously stirring until it boils.
Then continue over fast heat without stirring until liquid reaches temperature of 27° above boiling point of water.
Cool to 110°.
Stir until gloss barely begins to disappear.
Rapidly stir in nuts and pour immediately into buttered tin.
Enjoy!

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and soda into a bowl.
Add oil, eggs and 2 cups of apples.
Beat with mixer until batter is thick.
Stir in 2 more cups chopped apples and nuts.
Pour in large, greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine egg, milk, corn and butter; stir.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot shortening.
Fry 4 to 5 minutes or until golden brown; turn once.

title: curried shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In skillet cook onion, celery and garlic in shortening until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes and sauce, salt, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Simmer covered for 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon cold water.
Stir into sauce; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add shrimp and green peppers.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: dutch babies
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter into pie plate first.
Mix remaining ingredients until creamy.
Pour into pie plate.
Put into oven for 12 minutes at 400°.
Top with powdered sugar.
Great dessert!

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Thoroughly drain all fruit.
Place fruit in buttered casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle brown sugar over fruit.
Mix together butter and curry.
Dribble over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Lightly grease deep dish pyrex pie plate.
Mix Bisquick and milk, pat dough on plate.
Layer sliced tomatoes on dough. Sprinkle seasoning, garlic powder, basil and salt and pepper on top.
Mix cooked bacon, mayonnaise and cheese, spread bacon mixture on top.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: layered taco salad
directions: Layer lettuce, tomatoes and chips, then browned beef with seasoning. Melt cheese and add on top of beef. Serve immediately.

title: crawfish etouffee(serves 6)
directions: Saute onions in butter about 15 to 20 minutes until soft.
Add crawfish fat and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until fat comes to the top.
Add tails and season to taste.
Add just enough hot water to etouffee for desired consistency (use cornstarch to thicken if too thin).
Simmer 20 minutes, add parsley.
Serve over steaming hot rice (also good over pasta).

title: mom's butterscotch sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan brown sugar, flour and salt.
Add water.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter (thin with cream or half and half until desired consistency).
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Serve over devil's food cake.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl; beat until creamy. Prepare pudding mix with milk, using package directions.
Add pudding and whipped topping to cream cheese mixture.
Mix well. Alternate layers of cookie crumbs and cream cheese mixture in new 1 gallon plastic flower pot, beginning and ending with crumbs.
Place bouquet of red, white and blue silk flowers in pot and attach toy shovel.
Chill; shovel to serve.
May also half the cookie crumbs, use all the cream cheese mixture and remaining crumbs in 9 x 13-inch dish.
May use poinsettias for Christmas.
Yield:
25 servings.

title: hot homemade german potato salad(ala barbara sandquist)
directions: Use a large skillet.
Fry bacon until crisp (not burned); remove and set aside.
Drain all but 3 tablespoons of drippings; cook onions in drippings until clear and tender.
Stir in flour; blend well (still under low to medium heat).
Add vinegar and water; cook and stir until slightly bubbly and thick.
Add sugar and stir until it dissolves.
Crumble bacon into tiny and small pieces; gently stir crumbled bacon and sliced potatoes into heated mixture in skillet.
Heat thoroughly, stirring to evenly coat potato slices.
Serve hot or warm.
Yields 6 to 8 servings. "Totally Trumpy!"

title: chocolate chip cookies-my choice
directions: Cream margarine and eggs; add sugars and mix well.
Add flour with baking soda.
Add vanilla.
Stir in pudding mix, chips and nuts.
Add instant oatmeal or bran, if desired.
This will be very thick.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil sugar, cornstarch and water.
Boil until thick. Remove from heat.
Stir in jello; mix well.
Cool slightly.
Pour over fresh berries in pie shell.
Can make peach or raspberry.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well. Reserve 3/4 cup mixture for topping. To topping, add 1 cup nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. To cake mixture, add last 4 ingredients. Beat well by hand. Sprinkle topping over batter. Grease a 9 or 12-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: beef and cheddar macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef; remove meat and set aside. In same skillet, saute onion in margarine until translucent; drain fat.

title: taco pinwheels
directions: Mix sour cream, taco seasoning and cheese. Spread ingredients over all the taco shells. Roll each shell up and place in a freezer-safe container. Freeze until they can be sliced (about 1 to 2 hours). Slice each shell crossways. You may want to cut off each end and discard if serving on party tray. Serve refrigerated or at room temperature.

title: sweet potato and black bean burrito
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place sweet potatoes in medium saucepan with salt and water to cover. Bring to boil, then simmer until tender, about 10 minutes. Drain and set aside.

title: banana bread(4 loaves)
directions: Follow directions for Banana Bread.
I do not use my mixer on very low speed.
These can be baked in foil loaf pans sprayed with cooking spray for easier freezing, or wrapped in clear plastic and foil to freeze.

title: marinated cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Pour sugar over cabbage.
Heat vinegar and mustard, then add oil.
Pour over cabbage and sugar.
Add celery seed.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together to make crumbs.
Save 1 cup of the crumbs.
Mix the last 3 ingredients with the remaining crumbs.
Fill baking cups 2/3 full, then sprinkle approximately 1 teaspoon of crumbs on top of mixture in baking cups.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press rolls into a jelly roll pan (cookie sheet).
Bake until browned.
Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and Miracle Whip.
Spread on top of baked rolls.
Mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over top.
Slice in finger food slices.
Great!

title: "granny" hash browns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine potatoes, salt, 1/4 cup margarine, onion, pepper, soup, sour cream and milk in a bowl. Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° or 350° in a glass pan, for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; dot with 1/4 cup margarine and sprinkle with corn flake crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: christmas cubes
directions: Put candy and cookies in separate bags.
Crush with rolling pin until both are fine crumbs.
Mix into whipped cream.
Place mixture into an ice cube tray.
Freeze.
Cut into small squares to serve. Serves 8.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes for about 15 minutes or until soft. Put eggs to boil with the potatoes for 15 minutes and add a little salt. When potatoes are finished boiling, smash until creamy. Dice eggs and mix with potatoes. Mix in the mustard and relish. Once everything is mixed, smooth top of the salad and lightly sprinkle Tony's to taste.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans, lima beans and chopped onion.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Pour bacon grease into bean mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add additional sugar and barbecue sauce to suit your taste.

title: crusty baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant if you wish; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Sprinkle salt on both sides of slices.
Let stand for 30 minutes; rinse with water and pat dry.
In a pie pan, beat egg slightly.
In another pan, combine cheese, bread crumbs and parsley.
Dust each eggplant slice with flour, dip in egg to coat all over and dredge in crumb mixture.
Brush butter over bottom of a shallow-rimmed baking pan. Arrange eggplant slices in butter in a single layer.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 25 minutes, turning once to brown both sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hotel peabody vanilla muffins
directions: Combine sugar and eggs, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture and beating well after each addition.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Spoon into greased muffin cups or cups lined with papers, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs, fruit cocktail, nuts and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add the mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and flatten a little with fork.
Bake at 400° about 6 minutes.

title: texas brownies
directions: Combine the flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
In saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa. Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 17 1/2 X 11 jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until they test done in the center.
While brownies bake, prepare frosting.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes and put in baking dish.
Add sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Preheat oven to 375° and cook for 40 minutes.

title: greek salad
directions: Rub large salad bowl with garlic for flavoring.
Chop lettuce and combine with tomatoes, onion, green pepper and cucumber.
Mix; add olive oil and vinegar and mix again.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with black olives and chunks of Feta cheese.

title: mediterranean salad
directions: Cook barley 10 to 15 minutes until tender.
Drain and put in large bowl. Add scallions cut in 1/4-inch pieces, tomato cut in small chunks and olives coarsely chopped.
Drain peas and add to bowl with rest of ingredients.
Serves 10.
Serve chilled or at room temperature, 175 calories, 8 g fat and 0 cholesterol.

title: chicken marengo
directions: In Dutch oven, brown chicken in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover when it begins cooking, turn to low and cook 45 minutes or until tender.
Using handles of Dutch oven, shake now and then.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's "delicious dessert"
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Bake in pan at 325° for 15 minutes; let cool.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Tie the last 3 ingredients in a cheesecloth and float in wassail.
Simmer 15 minutes in covered pan. Remove spice bag.
May add 1 jigger of rum for extra warmth.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Shred and prepare by any method for cooked cabbage the cabbage.
Drain it well.
Prepare white sauce.
Prepare pepper and pimentos.
Saute and mince the bacon.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt bacon fat or butter.
Toss lightly in this the bread crumbs. Place layers of drained cabbage in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with the minced bacon, peppers and the cheese.
Cover with the cream sauce.
Top with the bread crumbs.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: peta-croation special
directions: Mix the dry ingredients as for pie crust, then cut in shortening, adding the well beaten eggs.
Knead dough and roll 1/2 of dough 1/4-inch thick.
Line cake pan with dough.
Spread apples over dough; sprinkle apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll out the rest of dough and place on top of apples.
Slit top dough. Bake about 1 hour in a 375° oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; cut in squares.

title: papa jim and grammie's fish batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Try 1 cup of soda first.
If batter seems too heavy, then add the additional soda. It should be the consistency of very heavy cream.
Dry fish fillets or vegetables, then dip in batter.
Deep fry in cooking oil.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper, celery and onion in oleo.
Combine with tomatoes and steam on low fire, 10 minutes.
Cook rice according to directions.
Place rice and tomato mixture in casserole dish. Mix in soup, garlic and parsley.
Stir in crawfish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes or until bubbling.
Don't stir.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: pepper steak
directions: Many husbands are spoiled by mismanagement in cooking and are not tender and good. Some women keep them in hot water too long. Others freeze them.
Some put them in a stew; others keep them in a pickle.
No husband will be good and tender if managed in this way, but can be truly delicious if properly treated.
Don't keep him in the kettle by force.
He will stay there himself if care is taken.
If he should sputter and fizz, don't become anxious.
Some husbands do this.
Just add a little sugar (the kind called kisses).
Never add vinegar or pepper.
A little spice improves him, but must be used with good judgment.
Do not try him with something sharp to see if he is tender.
Stir him gently lest he lie too long in the kettle and becomes flat and tasteless.
If you follow these directions, you will find him very digestible, agreeing nicely with you and he will keep indefinitely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cooked broccoli, rice, cream of mushroom soup and milk together.
Season to taste.
Pour into dish and top with Velveeta cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese melts.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine the ingredients, adding just enough ice water until the dough forms the right consistency.
Roll out on floured board.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple and juice. Add Cool Whip, then add marshmallows and nuts. Stir well; chill.

title: strawberry banana sugar-free pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, pudding mix and water and cook in microwave at High speed for approximately 10 minutes (stir at 5 minutes).
Time may vary.
Let cool.
Add strawberries and bananas.
Mix well and pour into 8 or 9-inch precooked pie shell.

title: tortilla snacks
directions: Squeeze all the water out of peppers.
Mix all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator 4 to 5 hours.
Spread on tortillas, roll as jelly roll.
Chill for a few hours, slice and serve.

title: lo-cal crab cocktail cakes
directions: In large bowl blend crab meat, 1/4 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup green onions and lemon juice.
Form mixture into 1 inch diameter patties.
Combine bread crumbs and dill.
Roll cakes in crumb mixture.
Place on large nonstick baking sheet and bake in preheated 375° oven 10 to 15 minutes.
In small bowl combine remaining sour cream and green onions.
Serve cakes garnished with lemon wedges; pass sour cream, green onion mixture.
Makes 16 to 20 (1-inch) crab cakes.
Nutrients per crab cake:
calories 46, protein 6 g, carbohydrates 2 g, total fat 1 g, cholesterol 25 mg, sodium 86 mg.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mix well and spread on rye bread.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Lightly toss together potatoes, cucumbers, onion and seasonings.
Remove egg yolks and chop egg whites and add.
Press egg yolks through sieve and combine with sour cream and Miracle Whip.
Add vinegar and mustard and fold dressing into potatoes.

title: patty's potatoes
directions: Layer in dish (13-inches).
Cook on 375° about 1 hour.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Melt butter. Stir in sugar and spices. Mix well. Pour nuts in large flat. Bake for 30 minutes at 275 degrees, stirring every 10 minutes. Store in tightly covered container.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Add milk and egg yolks (reserve egg whites for topping).
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked (cooled) pie crust.
Cool. Makes 1 pie.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and persimmon pulp. Mix well. Dissolve soda in hot water and add to mixture. Add flour, then milk. Add vanilla, pinch of salt and spices (if desired).
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 45 minutes in a 9
x 13-inch pan.

title: amish steak
directions: Cut the steak into thin strips.
Brown in a little butter until done, then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer until the pepper and onion are tender.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: hot bacon appetizer
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Spread evenly on toast rounds.
Place on baking sheet and broil 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add mushrooms and saute, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan, heat oil over medium heat; add onions and garlic and saute until onions are softened, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, 3/4 teaspoon salt and the bay leaf; mix well.
Reduce heat to low, cover and let simmer, stirring occasionally, for 25 to 30 minutes; remove and discard bay leaf.
In medium mixing bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta cheese, egg, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper, mixing well.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients thoroughly.
Form oblong balls out of hamburger mixture (about the size of a fist).
Roll cabbage leaves around balls of meat.
Place in large pot with lid.
Peel potatoes and carrots and place on top.
Add about 2-inches of water and season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 1 hour on top of stove.

title: buffalo-style chuck roast
directions: Place roast in covered roasting pan.
Combine ketchup, beer and brown sugar; blend thoroughly.
Pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of sheet cake pan.
Spoon in pie filling and spread.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Melt butter and drizzle evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and Karo; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and salt.
Blend well with beater.
Remove from mixer and stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Center should be rather firm and spring back when touched.

title: berry lite mousse
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water in blender at low speed until gelatin is dissolved, about 30 seconds.
Add ice; stir until partially melted.
Add strawberries; blend well.
Blend in whipped topping.
Pour into dessert glasses.
Chill about 2 hours. Serves 6.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Using small muffin tins fill almost to top.
Coat tins with Pam first.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° until thick.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine cream, sugar and butter in large pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stirring constantly, boil candy until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour candy into buttered pan.
Cut into pieces.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocado in medium bowl with lemon, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning mix.

title: nuts, bolts and screws
directions: Melt butter in large roaster.
Pour in Wheat Chex, Cheerios, nuts and pretzels.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and garlic salt.
Set oven at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.

title: apple pie, pie crust
directions: Place flour, sugar and salt in bowl and mix.
Add butter and shortening.
Mix until it resembles a coarse meal.
Slowly add water and mix until it comes together.
Gently press dough into a ball.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface and fix into 9-inch pie plate.

title: chocolate-cinnamon angel cake
directions: Bring egg whites to room temperature (about 1 hour). Meanwhile, sift flour, powdered sugar, cocoa powder and cinnamon together three times.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat the egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla with an electric mixer on medium speed until soft peaks form (tips curl).
Gradually add the sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating on high speed until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Transfer to a larger bowl, if necessary.

title: champagne dessert
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Mix dry instant pudding into the pineapple until thickened. Spread over cake. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: seiters venison pork sausage
directions: Cube meat for grinding.
Mix spices. Spread and mix with cubed meat.
Grind meat twice, once with chili plate, then with sausage plate.
Sausage can be made into patties or stuffed into casings.

title: cheesy broccoli-n-potatoes-n-foil
directions: In a 3-quart microwavable casserole, combine potatoes and water.
Cover and microwave on High for 13 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Cut 22 x 18-inch sheet of foil.
Layer potatoes, broccoli, onion, salt, pepper and cheese on foil.
Dot with margarine.
Wrap securely, using a double seal.
Place on gas grill 4 to 6 inches from coals.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the salt, pepper, water, sugar, vinegar and oil.
Let cool and mix with vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain well before serving.

title: rum raisin meringues
directions: Preheat oven at 275°.
Grease baking sheet.
Beat egg whites and rum flavoring until foamy.
Continue to beat, adding sugar gradually until stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add to warm applesauce.
Add flour and spices.
Add nuts and raisins which have been floured.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
At the bottom of the oven, place a pan of water in the center of the oven.

title: cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature about 2 hours. Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour, sour cream, orange rind, vanilla and lemon juice.
Whip heavy cream and fold into mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.
Drop temperature down to 250° for one hour.
Shut off oven and let cake stay in for another 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: orange delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Dissolve sherbet and add pineapple flavoring.
Chill
until	Jell-O	begins to gel; add fruit.
Whip cream and fold in.
Chill for 4 to 6 hours.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease only the bottom of a loaf pan. In a small bowl mix sweet potatoes, raisins and nuts and set aside. Mix dry ingredients together and blend.
Add lightly beaten eggs, oil and milk and blend with wooden spoon.
Lastly, add flavoring and sweet potato mixture and blend well by hand. Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool, wrap and store overnight for better slicing.

title: zucchini bread ii
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, add sugar and potatoes.
Stir until dissolved.
Let stand at room temperature all day or overnight before refrigerating.
Starter should be made 3 to 5 days before beginning bread.
Keep Starter in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days. Take out and feed with the following mixture.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, corn syrup and salt. Stir continuously until mixture comes to a boil.
Let mixture boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Slowly pour caramel over popped corn and optional peanuts.
Mix well.
Spread on 2 large baking pans. Bake, stirring every 15 minutes (250° for 1 hour).
Remove from oven and break apart.
Store in covered container.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: easy polenta
directions: Bring broth and water to boil over medium heat. Gradually add cornmeal. Reduce heat; cook, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes. Add cheese and cook until melted.

title: quick and easy pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shells.
Chill for several hours.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Place crumbs on bottom of dish and save 1/4 for the top.
Add milk and vanilla to Dream Whip;
beat on high speed until peaks form.
Warm cream cheese to room temperature and add to whipped mixture.
Whip until smooth.
Add sugar until blended.
Place 3/4 of whipped mixture on top of graham crust.
Add cherries, remaining crumbs and whipped mixture as blended topping.

title: "louisiana jambalaya"
directions: Chop all vegetables and saute onion, bell pepper and celery until onions are clear and bell pepper is tender.
The last minute of sauteing add garlic.
Set the vegetables aside.	Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces and season with Cajun seasoning (Konriko or Tony Chachere's).
Brown in bacon grease or butter.
Set chicken aside.
In the same pan, brown cut up sausage to get some of the grease out.
Leave some of the drippings in the pan and brown (stir while browning) rice until it's light brown.
Then add to your rice the vegetables, meats, chicken broth and some Cajun seasoning.
If using andouille sausage, add 1 teaspoon, if using regular smoked sausage, add 1 1/2 teaspoons and Kitchen Bouquet if the water doesn't look like it'll be dark enough (caramel brown).
Cover and cook on low-medium low for about 20 minutes.
Uncover and stir to check to see if rice is done.
Cook longer if needed.
Taste for seasoning and add more if needed.
Add green onions and stir. Serve with salad, garlic bread and sweetened ice tea.
Makes 8 servings.

title: victory sauce
directions: Heat syrup and milk.
Add remaining ingredients which have been mixed together.
Boil 2 minutes until sauce becomes thick.

title: black pepper shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in a baking pan and completely cover with the black pepper, then with sliced margarine.
Cover and bake in a 400° oven until shrimp turn red.
Turn shrimp over and cook other side.
When done, mix in juices and serve hot.
When peeled, the shrimp get the flavor of black pepper, but not the hot taste. Serves 4.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together sugar, butter or margarine and egg until light and fluffy.
Blend in milk. (Mixture will look curdled.)
Stir in self-rising flour and vanilla.
Spread half of the batter in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan which has been well-greased.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle half over batter.
Top with remaining batter and sprinkle with rest of brown sugar mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Sift first five ingredients.
Add to remaining ingredients and mix together.
Pour into muffin tins.
May use muffin cups. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen muffins. Freezes well.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery; add Veg-All, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix in baking dish.
Mix crackers and oleo, put on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a punch bowl, layer the ingredients in order listed, beginning with cake and ending with Cool Whip.
Use only one-half of each ingredient, reserving the other half for the second layer. Repeat the layer process, using the remaining one-half of each ingredient, ending with Cool Whip.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut steak into bite-size pieces.
Cook in skillet with a little oil until tender.
Add a small amount of water to make gravy.
Add onion mix and sliced peppers.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: fried pork chops in smothered onions
directions: Heat a large fry pan.
Coat chops with 1st egg, then flour. After adding salt and pepper to naked pork chops, sprinkle with garlic salt.
When coated with egg and flour, place in fry pan on medium heat.
Fry for 4 minutes on each side or until brown and juicy.
Fry onion until yellow with garlic salt.
Place over chops and cook 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse and drain blueberries.
Mix butter, 1 cup sugar, milk and flour in a 2-quart Corning Ware dish.
Place drained berries on dough.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake up to 1 hour.
Check for doneness by inserted knife in center.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add all other ingredients.
Pour into well greased 8-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix the baking soda with the chopped dates.
Pour the boiling water over the dates and baking soda.
Add the butter or margarine, sugar and salt; mix well.
Allow to cool.
Add the egg when the date mixture is cool and mix it in.
Add the remaining dry ingredients and beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix in. Pour batter into 13 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffing lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in skillet; drain fat.
Add 1 cup of the spaghetti sauce and the water.
Bring to a boil.
Add stuffing mix; stir to moisten.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg in a medium bowl; stir in Ricotta and Parmesan cheese.
Spoon in 1/2 of the stuffing mixture evenly in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spoon 1/2 the cheese mixture on top of the stuffing.
Top with 1/2 cup each of the Mozzarella cheese and the spaghetti sauce.
Repeat the layers. Bake 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavored stuffing mix

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together and add the beaten eggs. Add the crushed bananas and beat. Mix the soda with the buttermilk. Add the flour, salt, vanilla, and buttermilk mix to the banana mixture and bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix biscuits as usual.
Place 1 stick of margarine in bread pan and place in oven to melt.
Remove pan from oven and leave half of margarine in pan.
Use the rest to spoon over biscuits.
Bake at 375° until golden brown on bottom and top.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening with fork or	pastry	blender.
Add
buttermilk; mix well.
Put on lightly floured breadboard.
Knead lightly;
roll to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut
with
biscuit cutter.	Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: egg sandwiches
directions: Mix together.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: lemon icebox dessert
directions: Cook first four ingredients in double boiler, stir until custard sauce stage.
While hot, add gelatine which was dissolved in the 1/4 cup water.
Gradually fold stiff beaten egg whites into hot custard.
In well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan, pour a layer of custard, then a layer of angel food cake pieces and then custard. Top with whipped cream.
(Optional:
Sprinkle with coconut.)

title: tex mex meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 7 ingredients.
Spread into an ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain excess drippings.
Spoon chili sauce over cooked loaf, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake an additional 15 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Prepare and cook beans, then drain them.
Toss oil, vinegar, onion, salt, garlic and pepper into the beans.
Pour into an ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Mix butter, crumbs and cheese together.
Sprinkle over the beans.
Bake, uncovered, in an oven at 350° until heated through, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for exactly 15 minutes in 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: apple and spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat butter or margarine and sugars until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt by hand.
Beat until smooth. Stir in apple and oats. Drop batter by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake 12 minutes or until edges are golden.
Let cool on baking sheets 1 minute. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Stir together apples, celery, yogurt, grapes and mayonnaise. Just before serving, add walnuts.

title: roast pork and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pat the roast dry with paper towels. Combine the garlic, thyme, salt and black pepper.
Rub this mixture over roast.
Bake in oven for approximately 2 1/2 hours. Add potatoes; cook until potatoes are golden brown.
Remove roast to platter.
Cover and "rest" for 15 minutes before carving. Drippings can be thickened with flour and water paste, if desired. (Remove fat first.)

title: rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Add peanuts and marshmallows. Spread in foil lined 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat yolks of eggs until light and add.
Add milk.
Roll the crackers fine.
Mix baking powder with the cracker crumbs.
Add to other mixture together with salt and chopped nuts.
Add beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 layers in moderately hot oven (375°) until done.
When cool, spread whipped cream between layers and on top of cake.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto well greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill large mushroom cups which have been wiped clean and dipped in melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together and press 1/2-inch thick on cookie sheet.
When firm, cut into squares.
Roll in flour and fry in pan.
Pour a can of onion or mushroom soup over top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: diabetic chicken casserole
directions: Skin and cook by boiling or baking chicken breasts.
Let them cool and then remove bones.
Break chicken into pieces and put into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

Peel potatoes and cube them, cook together until done, then drain them and put the vegetables on the meat. Make gravy from chicken broth using arrowroot for thickening, then spread the gravy over the top of the vegetables.
Put in the oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, green pepper, mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Soften gelatin in water; dissolve over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Blend into potato mixture.

title: miracle whip salad dressing cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in sifter; sift 2 or 3 times.
Add cold water; beat thoroughly.
Add Miracle Whip and vanilla.
Bake in 2 layers at 350° or in a tube pan.

title: louisiana crabmeat quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium nonstick skillet, melt margarine.
Add peppers, mushrooms and green onions; cook, stirring frequently 3 to 4 minutes until tender.
Stir in crab and spoon mixture in the pie shell.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ketchup and honey; mix well. Turn mixture into a 7 or 8-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes until firm and brown on top.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix the first four ingredients.
Boil water and 1 cup sugar together, then cool.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Let it set overnight.
Drain.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over sauerkraut.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch pan.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and stir until smooth.
Put in large mixer bowl and beat 1 minute.
Add egg and vanilla. Continue beating until light and fluffy, scraping down sides of bowl often.
Stir in flour and salt until just blended.
Fold in chocolate pieces.
Put in pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in tube pan for 55 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Spread croissant dough on greased sheet cake pan (12 x 18-inch) or cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, yogurt and mayonnaise with Hidden Valley Ranch mix.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle with vegetables.
Cut into squares.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: Grate cheese to your own taste.
Whip cream and put over mashed potatoes.
Put grated cheese over the potatoes, approximately 15 minutes before serving.

title: strawberries dipped in chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate bark in double boiler; stir until all melted. Cool slightly.
Dip berries one at a time.
Hold by top or with inserted toothpick.
Allow to harden at room temperature.
It is best not to refrigerate because they tend to sweat so plan to dip berries the day you use them.

title: canine cookies for dogs
directions: In large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix yeast, bouillon and hot water until dissolved.
Add egg mixture and food coloring.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups of broth and yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Mix with hands until dough is quite stiff.
If dough is too firm, add more broth.
On well floured surface, roll out dough to 1/3-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes of bones, fire hydrants, slippers or doughnut holes.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes, until brown at edges. Turn oven off and leave cookies in oven overnight.

title: green salad
directions: Open pineapple.
Save liquid and mash pineapple.
Use liquid to make 4 cups for jello.
Chill.
While chilling, mix cream cheese, chopped pecans and pineapple.
Mix well.
Whip jello slightly.
Add Cool Whip to nut mixture.
Refrigerate.
It is better to prepare the night before you plan to use.

title: dirt cake
directions: Work cream cheese until blending consistency.
Add Cool Whip, then semi-set pudding.
Fold together until well blended.
Put in refrigerator.
Layer finely ground cookies with pudding mix, the final layer should be cookies (this should be done in a flowerpot).
Then put a plastic flower in the center and add gummy worms for effect.
Enjoy!

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Season veal with salt and pepper; dust with flour and shake off excess.
Beat egg with water.
Dip meat into egg mixture, then into bread crumbs.
Place in a single layer on a platter and chill in refrigerator for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Quickly brown veal (about 1 to 2 minutes each side) in a generous amount of hot melted butter and oil in a frying pan.
Place browned meat in a single layer in a greased shallow baking pan.

title: mom's raisin bread
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over raisins with 2 tablespoons butter. Set aside until cool.
Beat together sugar, egg and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Mix well with egg mixture.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix.
Bring to boil. Pour over apples.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let set until marshmallows are almost melted.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in mold and let set overnight.
Unmold right before ready to serve.
Top with cherries.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Mix nuts, coconut and jello together.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over and mix.
Form into strawberry shape.
Roll in red sugar crystals.
Dip end in green for stem.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat oil and butter in large saucepan.
Break onions into rings and add to pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and slowly saute onions until golden.
Add broth.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and sherry; stir.
Put in individual oven-proof bowls.
Top with toasted bread and cover with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: zip-n-zangy wings
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup Durfy's red hot and vinegar.
Heat.
Fry or bake wings until brown.
Drain.
Put wings in a large bowl and add sauce.
Stir until wings are coated.

title: taco meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve with toothpicks.
Yields 35 to 40 meatballs.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Combine ingredients (except fryers) into a saucepan; bring to boil.
Place fryers in a pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting several times with sauce.
Also good to cook on a grill.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add buttermilk; add one egg at a time and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Test with straw for doneness.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Cream margarine and gelatin. Beat well.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture, blending well.
Roll out cookie dough and cut.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together.
Add lemonade and a few drops red cake coloring for a pretty pink color.

title: famous peanut butter pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add gelatin mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: mom's round steak
directions: Cut round steak into individual serving sizes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Flour each piece.
Place in baking dish.
Top with onions and sprinkle with soy sauce.
Put in only enough water to cover top of steak.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours, covered.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: I use my cookie press, so easy!
Bake at 350°.
They should not brown so watch!

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Pour off grease and add other ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.
If too thick, add water.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
In large skillet brown onion, pepper and beef in shortening.
Add cooked noodles, soup, water, sauce and pepper.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll one package crescent rolls onto each cookie sheet.
Pinch seams making one large sheet.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes and cool.
Mix next four ingredients. Spread evenly over crescent pastry leaving slight border to achieve pizza effect.
Chop all vegetables and sprinkle over entire pastry.
Refrigerate.
Cut into 2-inch squares and enjoy.
Recipe can easily be cut in half and can be prepared up to one day ahead.

title: tasty little devils
directions: Brown hamburg and sausage.
Melt in cheese and season to taste. Spread on party rye bread slices and cube.
These can be frozen by placing slices on cookie sheet and freezing.
Cut in cubes and bag until ready to use.
Place on cookie sheet in oven to thaw.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Use a graham cracker crust.
Beat the lemonade in a bowl. Fold in the ice cream and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 4 hours in the pie crust.
When serving, you can add sliced fresh strawberries.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice, milk, sugar, salt, cinnamon and raisins to a boil stirring all the time.
Remove from heat or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: roast beef and vegetables
directions: Sprinkle onion soup mix in baking dish.
Place roast on soup mix and salt and pepper.
Place potatoes, carrots and celery around roast.
Add 1/3 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours or until roast is tender.

title: cretan shrimp
directions: Heat oil over medium heat in heavy skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until soft and transparent, about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, wine, 1 tablespoon parsley, oregano, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and cook briskly until pureed.
Add shrimp; cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes or until pink and firm.
Stir in cheese and remaining parsley.
Serve with pasta.
Serves 4.

title: flavorful rice dressing
directions: In a large bowl, lightly toss bread, corn bread and water. In a skillet, saute celery, onion and mushrooms in oil until tender.
Stir into bread mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a thermometer reads 160°. Yield: 8 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg until thoroughly combined.
Spread mixture evenly in pan.
Saute hamburg, onion and green pepper in oil in a large skillet until meat is brown, then drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti layer; top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top and bake another 5 or 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet. Add chicken. Stir in dressing mix.
Add vegetables and water. Stir-fry about 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: date refrigerator candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Cook until syrup forms a soft ball in water. Add chopped dates.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, until candy becomes very thick. The bubbles will pop and hiss and the mixture will follow the spoon around the pan.
Take from fire and add nuts and coconut. Beat until mixture is like soft cookie dough and can be handled. Turn out on a cloth which has been dipped in cold water. Roll to form a 1 1/2-inch cylinder.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop mushrooms, beef and olives in food processor.
Chop scallions.
Mix all ingredients and roll in chopped pecans. Serve with Sociable crackers.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Pour over chicken wings (large package), chicken breasts or chicken pieces.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 375°.
Great as an appetizer or as a main dish.

title: russian slaw
directions: Cut up all vegetables and set aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients; let boil 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage mixture and let sit in refrigerator in covered dish for 24 hours.
Slaw will keep for 30 days.

title: strawberry pie or fruit pie
directions: You can use blueberries, peaches or nectarines for the strawberries.

title: michigan hot dog sauce
directions: Cook onions in butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients in order; crumble hamburg in sauce and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes until hamburg is cooked.
Chop raw sweet onion to sprinkle on top of sauce after you put it on your hot dog.
This sauce freezes well or keeps almost indefinitly in your refrigerator.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Lay chicken in pan.
Cover bottom of pan with water.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Cook in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Then pour jar of barbecue sauce on top and cook for 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Boil the margarine, water and cocoa and pour over the flour mixture.
Beat well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla and mix well.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° in a greased and floured deep cookie sheet (jelly roll pan). Pour icing over cake and bake for 5 minutes more.

title: chili ron's way
directions: Cook ground chuck and sausage separately.
Drain to get all the grease off.
Dice onion and bell pepper; cook until tender. Add all ingredients to a 4 or 5-quart pan.
Add enough water so that your mixture does not stick to pan.
Bring to a boil; turn burner down on low heat.
Cook 30 minutes.
Stir often.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Eat with Doritos or crackers.

title: reed enchiladas
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion, garlic and chili powder.
Drain. Add 1/2 of the cheese and set aside.
Heat enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and tomato paste to simmer.
Spread 1/4 cup sauce mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

With metal tongs, dip each tortilla in hot oil to soften, a few seconds on each side, then in hot sauce mixture. Top each with small amount of meat mixture. Roll up and place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When done, pour remaining sauce evenly over enchiladas. Top with remaining cheese and garnish with green chilies. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with fried eggs and sour cream.

title: zucchini-tomato pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle zucchini, pepper, onion and tomato into pie plate.
Pour grated cheese over top.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth on high speed with mixer. Pour over other ingredients in pie plate.
Bake about 40 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° until brown and firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Cook and stir all but last 2 ingredients over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and nut meats. Cool until thick enough to spread, beating occasionally. Pour over cake while still hot.

title: chicken cutlets parmesan
directions: Pound cutlets to approximately 1/8-inch thick.
Dust cutlets with flour; shake off excess.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and oregano in another bowl.
Dip cutlets in egg, then in bread crumb mixture.

title: creamy pasta bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Bake cake as directed; cool. Crumble in bottom of large punch bowl. Pour pineapple on top of this. Mix up pudding as directed. Chill, but not firm. Pour onto top of pineapple. Chill until firm. Add cherry pie filling. Add whipped topping. Put cherry on top. Refrigerate.

title: florida brandy slush
directions: Heat water and sugar to dissolve and cool.
Put bags in hot water.
Let stand until cool.
Mix with lemonade.
Add brandy and freeze.
Fill glasses 2/3 full; add 7-Up and serve with a straw. Slush can be kept frozen indefinitely.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat 2 eggs fluffy.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini. Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder in a bowl.
Add to zucchini mix.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 large or 4 small loaves.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Don't overcook. Let cool. Whip cream cheese and sugar. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over pretzel crust. Mix jello, water and strawberries. Let cool. Pour over cream cheese layer.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl with a wooden spoon.
Add remaining ingredients except boiling water and stir well.
Add boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans or three 8-inch round pans. Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Or bake in one 9 x 13-inch oblong pan for 45 to 55 minutes (or cupcakes).
Cake is ready when inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool cake on rack.
Ice and serve!

title: orange and basil marinated swordfish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large baking dish.
Add fish to dish, turning to coat with marinade.
Marinate 30 minutes to an hour in refrigerator.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In skillet, heat oil.
Add broccoli, tomatoes, squash, carrots and garlic.
Cook on medium-high heat 1 to 2 minutes.
Add broth, parsley and basil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook on low heat about 5 minutes.
Add pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter and stir in sugar.
Cool and beat in one egg at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Then stir into brown sugar mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased pan, bake for 40-45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Be careful not to over bake.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Thinly slice slaw and mix with noodles.
In bowl, mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over slaw mix.
Toss and refrigerate overnight.

title: appetizer tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all of the filling ingredients together thoroughly. Divide filling and spread evenly over the tortillas; roll up tortillas.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, twisting ends of wrap to seal and refrigerate for several hours.
Unwrap and cut 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick (an electric knife works best).
Lay pinwheels flat on glass plate; garnish with parsley.
Leave space in center of plate for small bowl of salsa if desired.
Makes about 50 pinwheels.
I serve these at Christmas Open House.

title: chicken rice dish
directions: Put rice in deep roasting pan and cover with water 1 inch over rice.
Add soup mix and stir into rice.
Put chicken on top and pepper.
Absolutely use no salt.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer to brown chicken.
Try substituting pork chops for chicken.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until onion is clear.
Add cream of mushroom soup; mix well.
Place in an 8-inch cake pan; smooth top.
Cover with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese. Add cake flour and beat well. "Pitch in" eggs all at once. Beat well, then add vanilla last and beat more. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured Teflon Bundt pan.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; pour off excess fat.
Add onions.
Cook for 10 minutes on low heat.
Add seasoning.

title: raisin zucchini bread
directions: Finely shred zucchini to measure 2 cups; set aside.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add beaten eggs, zucchini and vanilla; mix well. Combine flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Add raisins and nuts to dry ingredients.
Combine with zucchini mixture; mix well.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: coconut mist cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter to soften.
Add flour mixture, milk and vanilla.
Mix until all flour is moistened, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add egg.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Stir in 2/3 cup of the coconut.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Split cake into 2 layers.
Reserve 1 tablespoon jam for garnish.
Mix remaining jam with 2/3 cup of the coconut and spread between layers.
Cover top and sides of cake with Cool Whip and remaining coconut.
Garnish with reserved jam.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Simmer onions in oil; brown some.
Pour in tomato paste and brown (7 to 8 minutes), stirring constantly.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: mexican salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Add beans, dressing and Fritos.
Spread cheese on top.
Layer as in above order; can layer again if making extra large batch. Refrigerate, but not over 6 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute sausage, beef, onion and garlic until well blended.
Add next 11 ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles.
Combine Ricotta cheese with egg, parsley and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
To assemble:
Spoon 1 1/2 cups meat sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange 6 noodles lengthwise over meat sauce.
Spread with 1/2 the Ricotta cheese mixture.
Top with 1/3 of Mozzarella slices.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups meat sauce over Mozzarella and sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Add in layers remaining noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture, 1/2 remaining Mozzarella and all meat sauce.
Top with Mozzarella, sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover with foil and bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Remove foil and bake 25 minutes more.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Take any kind of leaf lettuce and tear into small pieces. Fill a salad bowl.
Cut onions into small pieces with lettuce. Mix bacon grease, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Heat these ingredients in small skillet to boiling point.
Pour over lettuce while very hot just before serving.
Toss through salad.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until almost crisp.
Wrap bacon around water chestnuts; secure with toothpicks.
Place on baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chestnuts.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.

title: granny howell's pound cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together; beat well. Add soda, baking powder, vanilla, lemon flavoring and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add flour last and beat until dough is smooth. Bake in a Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: may-o-falfa
directions: Toss mayonnaise and alfalfa sprouts together just before serving.
Serve with crackers.
Mix the amount you desire.
Don't mix too soon, will get soggy.

title: tamale pie
directions: Combine biscuit mix, corn meal and water to form soft dough. Press on bottom and sides of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Stir together all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour over dough and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with cheese while hot.

title: edible christmas tree
directions: Frost cones.
Decorate with candy sprinkles.
Put gumdrop on top.

title: party punch for 40
directions: Mix all together in large punch bowl.

title: wassail(spiced cider)
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Strain into heatproof punch bowl, or use crock-pot or clean coffee urn to serve.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Combine noodles, drained tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt. Blend soup and milk; heat through.
Add cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with almonds.
Bake in 425° oven about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Season and stir in spaghetti sauce.
In an oblong dish, place the cooked spaghetti.
Hold back some noodles for top layer. Add ground beef and cottage cheese. Add remaining noodles.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix together cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thickens over medium heat.
Then, add gelatin, let cool.
Add chopped pecans and diced banana, pour into 2 (9-inch) baked pie shells.
Chill and garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: quick macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add flour and half and half. Add slightly heated chicken broth.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and Worcestershire sauce.
Add beer.
Heat well, but do not boil. Stir to prevent sticking.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine drained beans, pork and beans and veggies in 9 X 13 inch baking dish.
May top with sliced bacon if desired.
Bake at 350 degrees until soft and bubbly.
Add more ketchup if too dry.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cut oven off and leave longer.
Mix Cool Whip, softened cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Whip all together until smooth.
Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Spread pie filling over this.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Skoosh up bananas well with fork and set aside.
Cream sugar and butter together.
Mix in eggs and bananas.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add to banana mixture.
Mix well.
Add pecans and mix well.
Add a few squirts of ReaLemon juice.
Cover and set aside for 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake - raspberry topping
directions: Mix well like cookie dough. Pat into 9-inch round pan on bottom and sides.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and water in small saucepan.
Stir until comes to a boil; cool.
Soften cream cheese and whip with fork. Add Jell-O mixture, still whipping.
Add pineapple, nuts and baby food.
Mix well and fold in Cool Whip.
Mold and chill.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add oil and mix in flour.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pat out dough on pizza pan.
Makes 2 thin crusts.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello following directions or use juice from strawberries in place of water.
Add fruit and nuts to jello.
Put half of jello mixture in dish and jell.
When jelled, spread sour cream, then pour remainder of jello mixture on top and jell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise; fold in broccoli.
Pour into casserole; cover with crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in the warm water.
Prepare orange juice as label directs and pour into large bowl.
Slice bananas directly into juice.
Add pineapple (with its juice) and the sugar/water mix.
Pour into a suitable container and place in freezer.
Stir occasionally as it freezes to form a slush.
Serve in cups with spoons and maraschino cherries.
Keeps well and can be moved from freezer to fridge and back again to keep it from freezing solid. It's worth the effort.

title: chinese glob
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion, then mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: mama's candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes.
Drop in warm water to cover.
Let boil only until potatoes are hot all the way through, not soft, when stuck with a fork.

title: spice tea
directions: Can be fixed by the cup or by large amounts.

title: pink frozen salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Substitute drained fruit cocktail. This requires a large mixing bowl.
Put into smaller containers for freezing, such as Cool Whip container.
Set salad out about 30 minutes before serving.
Leftover can be refrigerated.
Stir before using again.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown beef in 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in tomato sauce. Combine in separate bowl the cottage cheese, sour cream and onions.
Spread 1/2 of noodles in a buttered casserole.
Pour remaining butter over noodles.
Cover with cheese mixture, then remaining noodles.
Spread meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix hamburger, cream of mushroom soup, potatoes, salt, pepper and milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in square, well-greased and floured pan. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cheese diablo wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Arrange 2-inches apart on baking sheets.
Bake in 400° oven for about 6 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Makee about 4 dozen.

title: audrie's oven potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes and rinse 3 or 4 times.
Add seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour over potatoes.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine fruits in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, butter and curry powder, stirring well.
Spoon over fruit.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until thoroughly heated.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas on plate.
Mix butter and sugar.
Add bananas and then 2 beaten eggs.
Add sour cream and flour with soda.
Last, add the nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil quickly.
Reduce heat to medium and boil 3 or 4 minutes or until a little dropped into cold water forms a soft ball (234°). Remove from heat.
Stir in rolled oats, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until hardened.
Store in refrigerator, if desired.

title: butter dips
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in square pan.
Measure flour, sugar and baking powder into bowl.
Add milk.
Stir until dough forms.

title: raisin crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
Line pan with sheet of wax paper and spray again with nonstick spray; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine 1 3/4 cups of flour, 1/4 cup of sugar and baking powder.
In small mixing bowl, combine milk, 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon butter, egg and vanilla; stir.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Using electric mixer at medium speed, beat until blended.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into pan and spread evenly; set aside.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add margarine, cheese and beaten eggs.
Mix and form into crust in 10-inch pie pan.
In skillet, brown beef; add onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar and oregano.
Cook on low 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt over cottage cheese and spread meat sauce over cottage cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Allow to sit 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: easy cherry biscuits
directions: Combine crushed cherries and 1/2 of the juice with sugar, until partially thick.
Open biscuits and place on greased baking sheet.
Press flat part of thumb in middle of biscuits, dip 1 tablespoon cherry mixture into each biscuit.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 17 to 18 minutes.
Serve warm.
Top with vanilla ice cream.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oleo and flavorings together.
Add flour and soda.
Fold in raisins and pecans.
Pour into two Bundt pans or one large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: magic muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce.
Stir the cereals and nuts together.
Sprinkle the melted margarine over the cereal, stirring well to coat all cereal pieces. Sprinkle the seasoned "no salt" over cereal and stir well.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 18 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: ooey gooey karo krispers
directions: Pour corn syrup, sugar and salt into a large saucepan. Stir over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to boil. Stir in peanut butter. Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal, corn flakes and crisp rice cereal. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan and let cool. Make fun shapes with cookie cutters; decorate with icing, jelly beans or colored sugar!

title: impossible reuben pie
directions: Layer beef, cheese and sauerkraut in buttered 9-inch pie plate. Place remaining 5 ingredients in blender, process until smooth. Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dipped peanut butter crackers
directions: Spread peanut butter between two crackers to make desired number.
Melt almond bark according to directions on package.
Dip in melted bark one at a time with tongs and place on wax paper to dry.
May use sprinkles to decorate before crackers dry.

title: funnel cakes
directions: A deep fryer works best but if you do not have one, use a heavy deep pan.
Pour oil into the pan until it is about 2 inches deep and let it get very hot but do not burn oil.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add cracked ice; let sit 5 hours or overnight.
Drain well and cook in syrup.

title: broiled chuck with lemon parsley sauce
directions: Preheat broiler 10 minutes with greased broiler pan in place. Wipe meat with clean damp cloth and rub both sides liberally with 1/4 cup lemon juice, then salt, pepper and garlic salt. Broil 12-inches from heat or with broiler on low about 25 minutes on one side and 15 minutes on the other for medium-rare.
Melt margarine. Add lemon juice, cayenne and parsley. Serve over very thinly sliced roast.

title: kelly's best cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake according to box directions.

title: do-nothing cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix with a spoon. Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream together. Pour half the batter into pan. Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter in pan and swirl it. Pour on rest of batter. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. While cake is warm, mix the sugar, vanilla and enough milk to make thin. Pour over cake.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix wet ingredients except margarine and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle poppy seed over chicken mixture.
Combine margarine and cracker crumbs.
Pour over everything.
Bake about 45 minutes or until chicken is done at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and cook 3 hours in a slow oven (325°).
For the last 30 minutes, remove cover.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in a bowl the brown sugar, flour, salt and pumpkin pie spice.
Add and stir until smooth the pumpkin, milk, egg and molasses.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan lined with unbaked pastry. Bake on center rack of oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon in greased muffin pan 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Place frozen or thawed roast in large container and pour vinegar over roast, then water.
If roast is not covered with liquid, turn several times while marinating for at least 3 hours. After marinating, wash meat thoroughly under cold water.
This draws all the blood out of the meat.
Pat dry and stuff with garlic.
Plug each hole with a little piece of meat to hold garlic in while cooking.
Salt and pepper the roast and place on grill over low burning coals.
The pit should have a cover.
Baste meat with salad dressing throughout cooking.
Cook at least 4 hours or until tender.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Beat eggs in saucepan.
Place over low heat.
Pour vinegar and water over eggs slowly.
Stir constantly until it boils.
Soak cucumbers in salt water for 2 hours.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In large skillet, saute ground beef and onions until brown. Drain.
Add Ragu and heat through.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange 4 noodles, 1/3 hamburger mixture and 1/3 cheeses.
Make 2 more layers, ending with cheese.
Pour boiling water around edge of pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Coat chicken with flour.
Cook in oil over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes or until brown; drain.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers.
Place in greased casserole dish and sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.

Cream together butter and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and lemon rind; beat well. Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in walnuts.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 55 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add the eggs.
Dissolve the soda in the sour milk and add.
Add mashed bananas.
Add flour and salt and bake in a loaf pan at 320° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken together and place into rectangular baking dish.
Arrange the chicken breasts into mixture in the dish so they are covered in it.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. After 1 hour, uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: spicy rice with black-eyed peas
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling in 10-inch skillet, breaking up tomatoes and stirring frequently.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until liquid is almost absorbed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients (except butter) in baking dish. Pour in fruit of your choice.
Put pats of butter on top and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: tortilla meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine meat, 1 cup of the picante sauce, oats, 1/2 cup of the tortilla chips, onion, egg, cumin, garlic powder and salt.
Mix well; press firmly into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Carefully pour off drippings.
Spread remaining 1/3 cup picante sauce over top of loaf; sprinkle cheeses and remaining chips.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: crock-pot smothered steak
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cut steak into serving pieces.
Trim fat and discard.
Coat each piece of steak with flour.
Lightly brown.
Coat bottom of crock-pot with 1/2 can of soup.
Layer steak, onions and soup; always end with soup.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: self rising flour mix
directions: Mix all together and use in place of 1 cup of self rising flour.

title: hobnobs
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat one egg white until fluffy.
Beat in 1 cup light brown sugar.
Add vanilla.
Fold in pecan halves. Cover nuts well.
Place pecans on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Cut off oven and leave in oven for 30 minutes.
Do not open oven.
(May be made with roasted peanuts.) Break in pieces.

title: pineapple pie(lighter eating - 2.5 points)
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pie crust.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix
shortening,
sugars, eggs, coconut, vanilla, soda, salt, flour
and oatmeal.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet
and
press into shape with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add tomato sauce, salt, lemon juice and grated onions.
When thickened and cooled, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ring molds.
Serves 6 or more.

title: mediterrain fish stew
directions: Melt butter and cook onions for 2 minutes.
Press garlic and add to onions.
Add flour until smooth.
Add tomatoes, water, carrots, chicken cubes, marjoram leaves, bay leaf and pepper. Cook until carrots are half done.
Add fish, mushrooms and green pepper.
Remove bay leaf and cook approximately 5 minutes, until fish flakes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: spicy sandwich loaf
directions: Saute green pepper in butter until tender.
Set aside.
On a large baking sheet lined with aluminum foil, press dough into a 10 x 13-inch rectangle.
