Layer ham, salami, cheese and pepperoni down the center of dough; top with peppers.
Fold sides of dough over filling, lapping the edges.
Turn seam side down; pinch ends together and tuck under to seal.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Brush with egg glaze if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all together. Store in a tight container. Use 2 teaspoons for cup of hot water.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Stir in 1 cup M&M's.
Reserve remaining candy for decorating.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets. Decorate the tops of the cookies with remaining candies.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: I add a small amount of salt (1/2 teaspoon?) and around 1 to 2 tablespoons cocoa.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook and stir all ingredients except beets.
When thick and clear, add the beets.
Place pan over hot water for about 30 minutes.
Just before serving, heat again and add 2 tablespoons butter.

title: braunschweiger
directions: Heat beef bouillon and Knox gelatine together, then cool.
Mix cream cheese, braunschweiger, mayonnaise and onion salt or onions with first mixture in a blender.
Chill overnight.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into a tube pan and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Easy, fun, colorful and delicious.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Cool and slice long ways in half. Spoon out inside and put in bowl.
Add onions, margarine, crackers, milk, salt and pepper.
Mixture should be moist.
Put mixture in squash shell and bake.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: new peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large saucepan over low heat, stir together the first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil for about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; toss to coat well.
Press into pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash and slice	zucchini
and onions; cover with 1-inch cold water.
Add salt
and
let	stand
for
hours.
Drain. Combine remaining ingredients
and bring to a boil.
Pour over zucchini and onions.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Bring mixture to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pack in hot pint jars.

title: date pudding
directions: Cook 1/2 pound of dates, baking soda and 1 cup hot water until dates soften.
Cool.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, butter or margarine and 1 egg.
Add this to date mixture.
Add in flour, baking powder and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cook remaining 1/2 pound of dates, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water until soft.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and spread over top of pudding.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: barbecued burger cups
directions: Combine ground beef, barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar. Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Press biscuit into muffin cup until it comes up to the edge.
Spoon in meat mixture then add Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake very slowly in large pan for about 40 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add mashed beans.
Sift all dry ingredients together; add to sugar mixture.
Add apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until done.
May be baked in oblong, tube or Bundt pan.
Good plain, or frost with caramel icing.

title: chili sauce for hot dogs
directions: Fry hamburger until very fine.
Add rest of ingredients to the hamburger.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Put on hot dogs with mustard and onions.

title: perfect pastry
directions: Mix in order given.
Crisco should be the size of peas.
Roll out into size desired.
If 2-crust pie, brush top with milk.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 375°.

title: cran-grape-tea punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags and spices; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags, squeezing gently; remove and discard spices.
Add fruit juices and sugar.
Stir mixture until sugar dissolves.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 5 cups.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add cream cheese, pineapple, Coke and nuts.
Stir until cheese dissolves.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: iced rice
directions: Measure rice and place into boiling water for 6 minutes. Measure milk and heat with vanilla until boiling.
Measure sugar. Whip cream.
Place mold into fridge.
Put rice in milk and simmer 20 minutes.
Add sugar and simmer 5 minutes.
Soften gelatin in cold water and whip into hot rice.
Place in fridge.
When cool and thick, add whipped cream and put in mold.
Garnish with fruit. Serves 8 to 10.

title: seafoam or divinity
directions: Cook together until firm-ball stage or until syrup spins a thread when dropped from the edge of a teaspoon. Pour over 1/2 of syrup mixture. Return remaining syrup to burner and cook until hard-ball stage. Pour remaining syrup over egg white mixture. Beat until mixture starts to lose its gloss or until the mixture tastes grainy. Add nuts or dry fruit as desired. Walnuts or pecans work well.

title: ham ball
directions: Stir all ingredients together; chill.
Shape into ball. Roll in parsley flakes and pecans.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out liquid.
Combine sour cream, dressing mix, spinach and bacon bits in a bowl.
Spread filling on tortillas and roll like a jelly roll.
Lay on sheet pan with seam down.
Cover well and refrigerate at least 5 minutes.
Slice diagonally and serve.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Melt butter.
Whisk in flour constantly, about 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients, whisking occasionally until cheese is melted.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add orange juice, oranges and pineapple.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until solid.
Beat pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on gelatin layers; top with nuts.
Yields: 12 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package and drain.
Add dressing and all other ingredients.
Toss and chill before serving.

title: crabmeat stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute finely minced onions and pepper in a little butter.
Mix remaining ingredients together, except mushrooms.
Mix well. Remove stems from mushrooms and wash mushroom caps.
Stuff the mushrooms with the mixture.
Place in a baking dish with 2 tablespoons of water.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes. Sprinkle with ___, if desired.
Serve hot.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, brown sugar, water and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Blend in oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Place squash in salted water and let stand 1 hour.
Drain; set aside.
Combine in large container the sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add other ingredients and let come to a boil again.
Put into jars and seal.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press rolls flat on baking sheet.
Bake at 375°F for about 11 minutes.
(Ovens vary, just watch until crust browns, not burns!) Cool crust.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and dressing mix together until smooth.
Spread mixture over crust.
Top with chopped veggies.
Cut and serve.

title: breakfast loaf
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, bananas, vanilla and sour milk.
Sift together flour, bananas, vanilla and sour milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture.
Fold in, do not beat with a mixer.
Add nuts.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until springs back or toothpick stuck in the middle comes out clean, in oblong dish, or make in loaf pans.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in ungreased 11 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Press canned biscuits into muffin tin, molding to the sides. Fill each biscuit with sausage and barbecue sauce.
Bake until almost done.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and finish baking.

title: caramel heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake.
Punch holes in cake while still warm.
Spread caramel topping on.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Mash candy in a plastic bag.
Sprinkle on top of cake. Refrigerate.

title: johnny marzette
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix with celery soup, tomato soup, 1 can water and garlic salt to taste.
Add hamburger mixture to macaroni and mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° until bubbly, then cover with the cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Trim the fat off the chops and brown the fat.
Remove fat from pan and lightly brown the chops in the grease.
Remove chops and lightly salt.

title: american crisp cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Beat in oil and egg.
Sift flour with salt and baking soda; add to batter.
Combine well with remaining ingredients.
Drop one tablespoon at a time on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet. Makes 7 dozen.

title: lemonade dessert
directions: Crush the Ritz crackers and the sugar and melted butter and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the lemonade, milk and Cool Whip and pour over the Ritz crackers.
If you wish, you can save a few of the crushed crackers and sprinkle a few on top of the dessert.
This is a very cool and refreshing dessert!

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine and mix first 3 ingredients for filling.
Slice onions and combine with grated cheese and chicken.
Dip tortillas in hot grease to make pliable.
Place thin layer of filling on bottom of 2 (8 x 12-inch) baking dishes or grease bottom if preferred. Place large spoonful of filling on 1/2 of tortilla.
Top with cheese, onion and chicken mixture.
Roll tortillas and place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Repeat until dish is filled with 9 small enchiladas or 6 flour enchiladas, depending on which you use.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cut cheese into small chunks.
In large boiler, combine cheese, chili and salsa. Heat until cheese is melted. Serve with chips.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Grease and flour stem pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° on low rack on oven.
(Test as some ovens differ.) Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Add flour first and last.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put 15 cookies in food processor or blender.
Place in oblong pan.
Mix cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar and nuts.
Spread over layer of cookies.
Then spread Cool Whip over this.
Top with remaining 15 ground up cookies.
Keep refrigerated.

title: belgian beef carbonnade
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll beef cubes in this until well coated.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onions; saute until soft and tender.
Remove.
In same pan over high heat, sear beef cubes, a few at a time.
Return onions and meat to pan. Set on low heat.
Add garlic, bay leaf, thyme and celery. Sprinkle on parsley; add sugar and beer.
Bring to simmer while stirring.
Cover and poach on low heat, 1 1/2 hours.
Add vinegar. Simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, mix cheese, sugar, flour, peels and vanilla at high speed until smooth.
Beat in eggs and yolks one at a time, scraping bowl often.
Add heavy cream and blend well.
Bake in lower oven at 250° until toothpick comes out clean.
Use a graham cracker crust and your favorite topping.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Makes 2 layer pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Batter is thin.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry-raisin pie
directions: Combine cranberries, raisins, sugar, water and tapioca.
Cook on medium, stirring constantly about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Line 9-inch pie pan with half of the pastry dough.
Add filling; top with remaining pastry (lattice work top looks great).
Cut slashes in center.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos with rolling pin.
Set aside.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip, then add creamed mixture and mix well.
In big plastic flowerpot, invert Cool Whip lid in bottom so pudding won't come out holes.
Layer cookies in bottom, creamy mixture in middle and then cookies on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. When ready to serve, stick plastic flower in middle and serve with a garden trowel.

title: orange ball candy
directions: Mix together in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300°
for 25 minutes.
Stir together until cool enough to handle. Roll into 1 inch balls and then roll into powdered sugar.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt & vanilla, beat well. Add eggs one at a time, beat well after each addition. Stir in flour. Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours. Cool before removing from pan.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In a large shallow pan, place chicken, skin side up, in single layer.
In a bowl, mix together dressing, soup mix and preserves. Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350°, basting occasionally, about 1 hour or until tender.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken when serving. Serves 8.

title: white onions (french glazed)
directions: Place onions and bouillon or broth in a saucepan, covered. Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes or until onions are tender. Remove onions to shallow baking dish (reserve broth for another use).
Combine sugar, mustard, salt, paprika and melted butter. Mix well and pour over onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Use enough broccoli to cover a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken meat on top of broccoli.
Put cheese over this, then layer crushed cracker crumbs mixed with lots of melted butter for top layer. Bake at 350° for maybe 1/2 hour to 40 minutes to heat through.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate the cheeses together.
Add the onion, pimento and garlic salt; mix well.
Roll in toasted sesame seed, parsley flakes or chopped nuts, or a combination of these 3 items.
Enjoy.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion and saute.
Blend in flour and slowly add milk.
Stir until mixture boils and thickens. Add salt, pepper and mustard.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking pan, place 1/2 the potatoes and sausage.
Pour half the sauce over this layer.
Add the other half of potatoes and sausage and pour over the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Put some sausage slices on very top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately as directed. Melt margarine and saute onion and celery. Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 or 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: roasted bell peppers
directions: Cut each pepper in half.
Core and seed.
Flatten each half slightly with palm of hand.
Line baking sheet with foil.
Lay peppers skin side up in a single layer on foil.
Place under preheated broiler 3-inches from heat source.
Broil until charred black.
Remove and place in plastic bag and seal well for 15 minutes to steam peppers.
Remove from bag.
Slip off and discard skin.
Use in any recipe calling for roasted peppers.

title: chocolate blender pie
directions: Blend all ingredients (except butter) in blender until smooth. Melt butter and blend into mixture.
Pour mixture into 2 (8-inch) pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pies usually rise and crack and will fall when they cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Separate biscuits and cut each into quarters.
Place 1/2 of the cut pieces and 1/2 of the sugar/cinnamon mix into plastic bag and shake to coat pieces.
Set aside.

Do same with the other 1/2 of the biscuits. Grease a bundt pan. Place the first half of the coated biscuit mix in the pan and pour 1/2 of the hot butter mixture over biscuit pieces. Place the remaining biscuit mix in the bundt pan and repeat covering with the hot butter mixture. Bake 40-45 minutes @350 degrees, unmold right away.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring (if desired).
Pour into crust.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and chill. Spread whipping cream on top.
Garnish if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

directions: Heat oven to

with a fork until well blended.
Stir in Wesson oil and vanilla; blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Add
flour, which has been sifted with salt and baking
powder.
Drop

cookie sheet.
Press flat with bottom of glass dipped in
sugar (lightly oil glass, then dip in sugar). Decorate with
pecans,
chocolate bits or colored sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes;
remove immediately from cookie sheet.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain fat.
Grease 2-quart casserole or large pie pan.
Add soup, meat and peas.
Mix well.
Beat mashed potatoes with egg.
Spread evenly over meat mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be doubled and put in 8 x 12-inch cake pan.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Combine sugar and next 8 ingredients in a jar or any plastic container with a tight lid or cover, shake vigorously.
Pour over tomatoes.
Cover and chill 8 hours, spooning marinade over tomatoes.
Quarter tomatoes. May arrange 3 or 4 wedges on lettuce.

title: date cakes
directions: Cook dates in boiling water with soda until soft; set aside. In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and nuts; mix well.
Stir together flour and baking powder.
Add alternately to egg mixture with date mixture.
Pour into metal 8 x 8 inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine strong coffee with powdered sugar for a mocha-like frosting.
When cake is cool, put on a plate and frost.
Sprinkle top with red and green sprinkles.
Yields 9 pieces.

title: creole bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with mixer on high speed about 3 minutes.
Grease pan with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.
Let cool, then serve.

title: stir-fry pasta oriental
directions: Cook pasta according to directions and drain. Heat oil in wok or skillet. Add garlic, scallions, celery, and carrots. Cook and stir until translucent, but still crisp. Combine cornstarch, sherry, soy sauce and chicken broth and add to wok. Cook, stirring constantly, for one minute. Add water chestnuts, chicken, pepper, red pepper (if desired), walnuts, and cooked pasta. Gently stir and cook one minute.

title: hot honey in fruit tea
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add tea bags, cloves and cinnamon stick.
Cover and steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags, cloves and cinnamon stick.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat through.
Enjoy!
Yield: 4 (6 ounce) servings.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Place in crock-pot and simmer 4 hours or on stove for 2 hours.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Slice cake to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat together 1st four ingredients.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.
Pour over angel food cake.
Crush candy and sprinkle over the top.
Chill overnight.

title: confetti rice salad
directions: Add oil, vinegar, lemon juice, salt and mustard to hot rice. Stir in vegetables and season to taste.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion in pan; set aside.
In casserole dish, combine remaining ingredients.
Add sausage and onion mixture. Cover top with slices of sharp Cheddar cheese.
Do not cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix together and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: cajun deviled eggs
directions: Combine egg yolks with all ingredients, except paprika and olives, until blended.
Spoon filling into each portion of egg white, rounding off top.
Sprinkle with paprika and top with an olive slice.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Set aside 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Roll into small balls. Melt chocolate in double boiler or in glass bowl in a pot of hot water. Put small amount of chocolate in small paper cups. Put a ball of peanut butter mixture in the chocolate. Coat each ball of peanut butter with chocolate.

title: braunschweiger dip
directions: Cube and chop braunschweiger.
Cream everything but onion; add that after dip is beaten smooth.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: cicy's orange-cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large punch bowl.
Add ice cubes. Garnish with orange slices.
Yields 12 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Boil noodles and add to ground meat.
Add green beans, corn and cheese from macaroni and cheese package.
Stir together.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Season with salt and red and black peppers.
Top with Durkee onions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops or pork steaks and pour off drippings.
Cover with 1 layer of onion and add one layer of potatoes.
Pour cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press
a crisscross on each cookie with fork prongs dipped in water.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
In a 5-quart pan, saute onion and celery in portion of butter.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz, mushrooms and remaining butter.
Add 3 cups of cooked rice and broccoli (drained).
Pour into greased casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole i
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef until lightly browned. Add onions and chili powder and saute until tender.
Mix soups, enchilada sauce and milk in large container.
Stir until blended. Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place 1/2 of the tortilla pieces in bottom of dish.
Top with 1/2 of meat mixture.
Pour on 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Place 1/2 cheese slices on top.
Repeat with remainder of ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes. Freezes well.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn relish
directions: Drop ears of corn in boiling water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Dip in cold water.
Cut from cob; measure, there should be 10 cups. Combine corn with remaining ingredients and boil 15 minutes.
Pack into sterilized Kerr jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Put on cap, screw band firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 pints.

title: banana cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together in bowl; set aside.
In blender, put remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Cover and process on high until smooth.
Add nuts; process 2 minutes.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into baking pan; bake for 35 minutes, or until done.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: bright bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; stir in peanuts and salt.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir after first 4 minutes.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla; stir.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes more on High.
Syrup will be very hot.
Add soda and stir.
Pour on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush or grind cookies.
Blend remaining ingredients with mixer.
Layer cookies and pudding mix in a new 6 or 7-inch flower pot or plastic container.
Keep enough cookie crumbs out to put on top.
For decoration, add artificial flowers and gummy worms! Delicious!

title: strawberry sauce(low-fat)
directions: Place 2 cups strawberries in a blender.
Add water, maple syrup and lemon juice.
Blend until pureed.
Transfer to bowl and stir remaining 1 cup strawberries.
Serve over pancakes, French toast and waffles.

title: cough syrup
directions: Mix altogether and bring to a boil.
Boil until mixture is boiled
down by half.
Remove from heat, leave cinnamon and whole cloves
in, cool and leave in refrigerator.

title: sherried fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit and nuts into small pieces.
Use 1 1/2 cups sifted flour to coat fruit.
Melt butter and add sugar.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix flour and butter in saucepan.
Add broth and heat.
Cook to bubbling about 5 minutes.
Take off fire.
Add whipping cream, chicken and mushrooms.
Mix in spaghetti and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese.

title: easy yellow cupcakes
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla. Spoon batter into lined muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Beat eggs and sugar together until thick.
Stir in oil and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to egg mixture. Beat just until blended.
Roll dough on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep hot grease (375°) about 1 1/2 minutes on each side until golden brown. Drain on paper toweling.
Cool slightly.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate nugget cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar. Add shortening. Mix well. Add about half of the milk, beat 2 minutes, add remaining milk. Add eggs, beating after each addition. Add melted chocolate, beat 2 minutes. Stir in nuts. Bake in preheated 350 oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Yield: 3 layers. Cool and frost with fluffy white icing.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour and vanilla.
Grease jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Spread batter on cookie sheet.
Cut squares with knife (24 squares).
Dot each square with a heaping teaspoonful of pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: french raisin toast
directions: Preheat griddle on setting 9 to 10.
In shall bowl blend eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla, nutmeg and salt. Dip each bread slice in egg mixture, turning to coat both sides.
Lightly grease griddle. Cook bread slices 4 to 6 minutes, or until deep golden brown. Top with confectioners sugar or serve with syrup. 4 servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; blend until smooth. Fold in last 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with the tines of a fork; bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: kate smith coffee cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, melted butter and milk.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir into batter. Add 1 cup bran flakes.
Spread into a greased 8-inch baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl to make topping. Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Layer all ingredients until finished.
Crumble small amount of cake in bottom of punch bowl. Spoon pudding over cake, then pineapple, Cool Whip, cherry filling and walnuts.

title: homemade condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Makes the same amount as a store bought can.

title: easy fudge
directions: In a saucepan, heat together butter and water to boiling, stirring to melt butter.
Sift together sugar, dry milk and cocoa. Stir until mixture is nice and smooth.
Add the butter mixture, stir until well combined.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover and chill several hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: one dish chicken and stuffing
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package; set aside. Place chicken in baking dish; cover with Swiss cheese. Spread soup over chicken and cheese. Spoon stuffing mix over all ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: banana cake with coconut topping
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch round cake pan or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.

title: rice casserole
directions: Fix rice as on the box.
Brown onion in margarine.
Add mushrooms, bouillon cube and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted. Mix sauce and rice together.
Add milk and mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Mix flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt.
With mixer, beat butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until thoroughly blended.
Beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in peanut butter cup pieces and chips. On an ungreased cookie sheet, space 1-inch apart.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Chop onion very fine, cut hot dogs into 4 or 5 pieces.
Mix all ingredients, simmer for 45 minutes. Tip - use fondue pot.

title: playdough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add beaten egg.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, spices and salt.
Add alternately with the soup.
Stir in raisins.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: "fried" chicken(microwave)
directions: Finely crush round buttery crackers.
Remove skin and cut away any excess fat from chicken thighs.
Place butter or margarine in pie plate.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook at High (100%) power 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until butter melts.
On waxed paper, mix crumbs, paprika, salt and rosemary.
Dip chicken thighs in butter or margarine, then coat with cracker-crumb mixture.
Arrange coated chicken thighs on rack in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover dish with waxed paper.
Cook at High 9 minutes.
Remove waxed paper and rotate dish a half turn.
Cook at High 5 to 7 minutes longer until thighs are tender.
Let thighs stand 5 minutes before serving. Contains 440 calories per serving.
A good source of niacin and iron.
Serves 4. Time:
About 40 minutes before serving.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Into cupcake tins, lined with paper or foil, place a vanilla wafer.
Mix together in a separate bowl the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour onto the wafer.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.
When cool, spoon topping of your choice on each.

title: baked corn and bread
directions: Mix butter or margarine, eggs, both kinds of corn and sour cream together.
Add Jiffy corn bread mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Blend above ingredients in blender.
Add 1 cup shredded cheese, diced ham, crumbled bacon, shrimp or any combination.
Add cooked vegetables, if desired.
Pour into pie plate and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious chicken breast
directions: Spread chicken breast with fat from sour cream or low-fat margarine.
Season to taste.
Bake at 375° uncovered for 45 minutes or until tested done.

title: lettuce layer salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces in rectangular glass dish. Sprinkle onion and Salad Supreme on lettuce.
Spread peas over lettuce.
Spread Miracle Whip on top to cover entire salad.
(Use more Miracle Whip, if necessary.) Sprinkle sugar over all of the Miracle Whip.
Layer cheese and bacon on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Do not cook peas.
Add all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Better if made the day it is to be served.

title: barbecued roast venison
directions: Trim all tough membranes from meat.
In Dutch oven, cover meat with water.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and onions.
Cook 2 to 3 hours, simmering until tender.
Remove to roasting pan.
Use liquid smoke, Texas Pete and barbecue sauce combined in blender. Cover meat with sauce in pan and cover with foil to seal pan. Cook for 45 minutes at 375°.
Foil may be removed for additional browning.
May use for pork roast; very good.

title: rachel kalberer's favorite butternut squash
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chili baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Continue baking 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Most of liquid should be gone.
Enjoy!

title: angel treat
directions: Crumble angel food cake into loaf pan.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Fold into softened cream cheese and powdered sugar that has been beaten until fluffy.
Fold into cake in flat pan.
Spread pie filling over the top.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Roll the size of a walnut. Press two ways with fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan and add water gradually, stirring constantly. Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring often, until raisins are plump and mixture thickens. Serve hot. Makes about 3 cups sauce. Excellent on ham or Ham Loaf.

title: ham and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine macaroni with rest of ingredients.
Put into baking dish and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Drain garden peas and rinse with cold water.
Cut up onion very fine and add to peas.
Add chopped boiled eggs and add salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Mix with small amount of Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: rio grande stew
directions: Brown meat in a heavy pan.
Add first 10 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cook until almost tender.
Skim off fat.
Stir in carrots, corn and undrained beans; arrange cabbage wedges on top. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Season to taste with additional salt and pepper, or any of the listed spices.
Serve with salsa.

title: bread(fat-free)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, Egg Beaters, Butter Buds and 1 cup of flour.	Beat until smooth.
Stir in rest of the flour and continue stirring until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in size, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Spoon batter in 24 muffin cups sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Fill each cup 1/2 full.
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spicy glazed carrots
directions: Heat oil in hot wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add peppers and stir-fry until darkened.
Remove and discard.
Add carrots.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir-fry 4 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in teriyaki and cook until carrots are glazed. Serve immediately.

title: delightful lemon squares
directions: Combine margarine
with
cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar
and
mix until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar, lemon
rind
and lemon juice; stir well.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup flour with baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Stir well and pour
over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly
browned and firm.
Cool on wire rack.
Dust lightly with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: good and easy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients except sugar. Beat eggs, adding the sugar in 3 portions, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and bake in flat pan for 20 minutes.

title: auntie judy's apple cake
directions: Mix granulated sugar, oil and eggs together for 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine flour, baking soda and cinnamon; add to sugar-oil-egg mixture.
Mix thoroughly with wooden spoon.
Fold in apples.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour round cake pans. Combine dry jello, cake mix, water and oil.
Mix with mixer.
Add eggs one at a time and mix.
Fold thawed strawberries into batter. Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake till golden brown for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely before frosting.

title: no bake breakfast bars
directions: Microwave:
In 2-quart bowl, blend sugar, honey and peanut butter.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until bubbly. Stir until smooth.
Stir in cereal and raisins.
Press into greased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chow-chow(hayden's salad)
directions: Mix first five ingredients and let stand one hour.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients, except flour and vinegar. Flour is to be mixed with a little vinegar before adding to mixture.
Let boil about 40 minutes.
Seal while hot.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Boil fettucini noodles in lightly salted water with a dash of oil added to keep from sticking.
Boil until tender.
Melt butter in a large frying pan.
Beat egg yolk.
Add cream.
Beat until blended and add to butter.
Heat to medium for 1 or 2 minutes. Add drained noodles and toss lightly, adding salt and pepper to taste and 3/4 cup of cheese.
Use remaining cheese for serving. Serve immediately.

title: pumpkin walnut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook onion and bell pepper over medium heat, stirring often, until onion is pale gold, about 5 minutes. Add pumpkin and broth.
Cover and cook over low heat until pumpkin is soft, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rice, breadcrumbs, walnuts, egg, parsley, salt, sage and pepper; mix well.
Spray a 4-cup baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Pack rice mixture into dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; bake for 25 minutes.
Run under broiler for 1 to 2 minutes, until lightly browned on top.

title: okra in oil
directions: *Note:
If canned or frozen okra is used, do not fry them in oil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the chicken, celery, mayonnaise, soup, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Place in a 2-quart utility dish.
Melt butter in a 2-cup measure; add to corn bread stuffing.
Add stuffing mixture over top of casserole.
Bake in microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Place the flour in a large bowl.
Make a well in the middle. Add the eggs and oil to the well.
Stir with a fork until mixed. Add the water a little bit at a time, until the dough is smooth and elastic.
Turn the dough onto a table.
Knead the dough about 10 minutes.
Kneading dough means to work and turn the dough with the heel of your hands.
Let the dough rest on the table for 30 minutes.
Roll the dough on a floured surface until it is about 1/8-inch thick.
Let the dough rest a few minutes and then cut into noodle shapes with a dull table knife or cookie cutters. Cook the pasta in boiling water for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain, but don't rinse.
Add your favorite sauce.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Discard seeds; grind peppers, measuring after grinding.
Keep juice from grinding and pour over peppers.
In saucepan, mix the sugar, vinegar and ground peppers and boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Certo.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: crab legs
directions: Place cream cheese on serving dish.
Mix ketchup, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cream cheese.
Drain crab meat and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook, cool and mash squash.
Add onion, eggs, sugar, salt, pepper and 1/2 butter.
Mix well.
Put in a small, buttered dish. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Add margarine and blend in milk and beat.
Add coconut and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 325°.

title: vegetable muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray muffin pan with Pam. Cook vegetables in salt water until tender. Drain and puree in blender with egg and bread crumbs. Pour into muffin pan and bake 30 minutes.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Chop fruit, nuts and wafers into small pieces with food processor. Add milk and cream until well mixed. Pour into glass pan and cool.

title: ham loaf for 70
directions: Put milk on crumbs; soak.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add meat and seasoning.
Mix well.
Place in baking pan.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown chuck and sausage.
Add Velveeta (heat on low heat until cheese melts).
Spoon mixture on bread.
Bake at 350° for 7 or 8 minutes.
(Can be frozen to heat later.)

title: cashew pimiento "cheese" sauce
directions: Blend cashews with about 1 cup of water until very smooth. Add remaining water and other ingredients and continue blending until smooth.
Heat over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix prepared cake batter, margarine and 1/2 can milk.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: wise owl egg casserole
directions: Mix together eggs, mustard, salt and milk.
Brown sausage and cut into pieces.
Put ingredients in casserole dish (13 x 9-inch) in this order:
bread, cheese, egg mixture and sausage.
Let stand, covered in refrigerator, overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: rice tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger in a skillet and drain fat.
Add cooked rice, tomato sauce, beef bouillon, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Place in a 3-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with grated American cheese.
Combine egg, milk, oil, flour, corn meal, baking powder, sugar and salt until smooth.
Spread over tamale pie mix.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: dessie's sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Drain beans and add to meat mixture. Cook slowly while adding other ingredients (do not overcook). Pour mixture over buns while hot and serve with mashed potatoes.

title: honeybee cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with fork or hands.
Bake in a large tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: old fashioned swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper roast; flour and brown in skillet. Pour water over roast and cook on low heat 4 or 5 hours. Can be put in crock-pot all night for dinner the next day.

title: hurry-up cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Heat milk and add butter, salt and vanilla.
Combine mixtures while hot.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and, while still hot, cover with coconut, brown sugar, melted butter and cream.
Broil until coconut is browned.

title: stump hole cake
directions: Dump cake
mix, softened margarine and one egg in bowl. Mix well and
gently press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
With hands, press in chopped pecans and set aside.

title: spanish sponge cake
directions: Combine butter and lemon rind in large bowl; beat with electric beater until light and fluffy.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar; beat after each addition until smooth.
Add 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and salt; beat until smooth.
Add remaining eggs alternately with flour; beat thoroughly after each addition.

Spoon into well-greased and floured 9-inch square cake pan; spread evenly. Combine almonds and cherries; sprinkle with the remaining sugar. Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 minutes or until golden brown. Yields about 9 servings.

title: etta's cocoa peanut logs
directions: Melt chocolate morsels with peanut butter in a heavy pan over low heat, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add Cocoa Rice Krispies, stirring until coated.
Press lightly in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool or refrigerate until firm.
Cut into log shape bars.
Yields about 36 (3 x 3/4-inch) bars.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook hamburg first, then add all the other ingredients.
Cook it for 1 hour, then serve.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, onion, green pepper and celery in bowl.
Heat vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour over mixture and refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Spoon onto 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with crumbled chips, cornflakes or bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine everything in a pot.
Cook until chicken is tender.

title: mexican chicken dish
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 of cheese and 1 can of soup.
Fill tortillas and roll up.
Put in baking dish (9 x 13-inch) and add remaining ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat
all
ingredients with a hand beater until smooth. (For thinner pancakes, stir in 2 to 4 tablespoons of additional milk.)

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with 6 flat tortillas.
Brown meat and onion with chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Add beans with juice; simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour browned meat mixture on top of tortillas; top with sliced Velveeta cheese. Cover with remaining tortillas.
Mix soup with Ro-Tel; add on top. Cover with foil; bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: old-fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium pan; bring to boil and cook over low heat until peaches are tender and mixture thickens. Pour peach mixture into a lightly buttered baking dish.
Set aside.
`Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle water evenly over flour mixture and stir well with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Shape pastry into a ball.
Cut into strips.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently press baked pastry in peach mixture.
Repeat in a lattice design over peaches.
Put back in oven for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix dry dressing mix and sour cream.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the beans and 1/2 the picante sauce.
Layer in glass casserole dish.
Mix together avocados, sour cream and 1/2 the picante sauce (does good in a blender).
Layer over beans.
Mix together tomatoes, onion, black olives and green chilies.
Layer over avocado mixture.
Put taco seasoning on this layer.
Top with grated cheese.
For best flavor, let set up overnight.

title: pig licking cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch, well-greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, until done.

title: (any) cobbler
directions: Mix up sugar, flour, butter and milk, then stir in fruit. Bake until brown on top at 400°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all with mayo.
Top with margarine and crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and squeeze artichokes; chop with fork.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Blend in blender or with mixer.
Chill several hours.
Cut apples into wedges and dip into above mixture.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Cook rice and onion in butter until golden.
Add bouillon, cover and cook 20 minutes.
(Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes as usual for rice.)
Add 2 tablespoons butter and oregano to taste.

title: mother mac's gingerbread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a greased pan (square).
Bake about 15 or 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping or lemon sauce.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies in a bag.
Place 1/2 of cookies in an oblong dish or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix pudding and milk on medium speed; add cream cheese, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and flavoring (do powdered sugar and Cool Whip a little at a time).
Pour in pan; add rest of cookies on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with dried beef and onion.
Add dash of garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Form into ball. Decorate with sliced olives.

title: bacon cheese fingers
directions: Remove crusts from bread and slice into three pieces.
Combine first five ingredients; blend well.
Spread cheese mixture over each piece of bread.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Makes 30 appetizers.
Serve hot!

title: no-boil peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend butter into syrup.
Stir in peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix until creamy.
Stir in sugar.
Turn onto pastry board.
Knead with hands until smooth.
Press into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds of fudge.

title: cracker jacks
directions: In a saucepan, mix together honey and butter; heat over low heat until blended together.
Stir often.
Place corn and peanuts in large bowl and mix together.
Slowly pour the honey-butter mixture over popcorn-peanut mixture, stirring as you pour.
Mix until popcorn and peanuts are well covered.
Spread mixture in a single layer in a large baking pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven (or until mixture is crisp).

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: In large bowl, measure all ingredients with mixer at low speed; beat until blended.
Increase speed to high and beat 2 minutes.
Spoon into baking cups and bake until toothpick comes out clean, 18 to 20 minutes, at 350°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add rice, soups and mushrooms; stir just enough to mix.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli-pea casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, drain well. Arrange broccoli in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, seasonings, cheese, onion and eggs. Pour 1/2 over broccoli, cover with green peas, then pour remaining soup mixture over peas.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, pepper and peas in order listed in large bowl.
Spread Miracle Whip over peas to seal in around edges. Sprinkle sugar over Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add pineapple and beat; add coconut and beat.
Add mixture to beaten egg whites.
Fold in; don't beat. Put into an icebox dish, a layer of wafers and a layer of mixture. Cover over with wafers.

title: our favorite caramel corn
directions: Lightly butter two cookie sheets.
Spray inside of paper bag with Pam.
Place popcorn in a large brown paper grocery bag (not of recycled paper).
In a 4-cup measuring cup, or 1 1/2-quart glass casserole, stir together the brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Cook in microwave oven on full power 3 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 3 more minutes, add soda and stir.
Add vanilla and stir.
Pour this syrup over popcorn in bag, stir thoroughly with a long handled spoon.
Place bag in microwave and cook 3 minutes, giving bag a good shake after each minute.
Pour corn onto cookie sheet and allow to cool.
Corn will lose stickiness as it cools.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Pour chicken broth over bread crumbs.
Let set 10 minutes; gently mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add bread crumbs and mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2 quart loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until juices run clear.
Makes 6 servings, 265 calories per servings.

title: baklava
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cinnamon, sugar and walnuts. Melt butter.
Place 1 layer of filo in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Brush with butter.
Continue for a total of 5 layers.
Sprinkle some of the nut mixture.
Continue in a pattern of 3 layers filo/butter and 1 layer nuts.
Finish off with remaining filo. Cut into diamonds.
Place a clove in each diamond.
Bake 30 minutes.
Raise temperature to 475°; bake for 15 more minutes, until golden.
Remove from oven.
Make syrup by simmering honey, lemon and water until thick enough to coat the back of a spoon. Cool syrup.
Pour cold syrup over baked filo.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: broccoli rice au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet or saucepan.
Saute onion and celery in butter until clear.
Add broccoli, soup, Cheez Whiz, drained water chestnuts and rice and mix thoroughly.

title: cinnamon fruit
directions: In a large bowl, combine juice, cinnamon and brandy extract; blend well.
Add fruits and toss gently.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Stir before serving.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add nuts and apples.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: crab meat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft.
Add flour and blend, then add milk and blend.
Remove from
heat and add egg yolk, crab meat, salt and pepper (dash) and grated cheese. Place in casserole, top with grated cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot-cabbage slaw(diet salad)
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Finely chop onion and celery.
Mix together in a large bowl.
In separate bowl mix together Sweet N' Low, pepper, vinegar, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Pour over shredded vegetables and refrigerate.
Yields 10 servings.

title: teresa's grandma's banana nut bread
directions: In bowl, blend all the ingredients.
Pour into greased, floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put into bowl.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
This salad freezes very well.

title: angels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, spread bread with cream cheese and roll up.
Cut roll in half.
Cut bacon slices in half and wrap around rolls.
Place on baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes.
Increase temperature to 375°.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Toss to combine and coat ingredients with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: sausage canapes
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into bite-sized balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit dessert
directions: Bring to a boil 1/2 cup water and 1/4 cup sugar until consistency of syrup.
Add 1 tablespoon mint and lemon zest.
Turn off and cool.
Mix together all fruits.
Pour cooled syrup mixture over fruit.
Add fresh ginger.
Let sit for 1/2 hour.
Divide fruit into tall glasses (can use champagne type).
Fill glass with champagne or dry grape juice to cover fruit.
Garnish with fresh lemon slices.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain. Add rice and carrot. Mix well. Simmer 1/2 hour. Top with soy sauce.

title: boiled cake pre w.w. ii
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and boil 5 minutes; let cool. Add flour, soda, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in 3-quart pan over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Remove. Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together over hot water. Spread over top of bars.

title: noodle-tuna casserole
directions: Place ingredients in casserole.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cream of peanut soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until soft, but not brown. Stir in flour until well blended.
Add chicken stock, stirring constantly and bring to a boil.

title: cajun style red beans
directions: Rinse beans; drain.
Cover with water and soak overnight. Next day, drain beans, cover with water and bring to a boil along with the ham hock.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are just tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer an additional 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove ham hock and cut into small pieces.
Return to pot.
Serve with hot rice and corn bread.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Combine partly thawed potatoes, soup, milk and 1/2 of onion rings.
Pour into a greased casserole dish; then salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle other half of onion rings on top before serving.

title: barbecue sauce no. 2(no. p-16)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer about 2 hours, stirring frequently, until sauce begins to thicken.
Add meat, which is about 1/2-cooked, to sauce at this point and simmer until meat is done.
Yields 2 1/2 gallons.

title: chocolate fudge(by hand)
directions: Place sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in a large heavy saucepan. Stir slightly and occasionally to keep from sticking.
Using a candy thermometer, boil until fudge reaches 232° (be patient). Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Let sit to completely cool, stirring occasionally.
When too thick to stir, pour fudge out onto wax paper and knead with hands.
(One-half cup chopped nuts can be added at this point if you desire.)
Flatten out on a buttered cookie sheet and cut into cubes.
This makes a delicious chewy fudge.
Store in airtight container.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Cut up onions and mushroom stems; saute in margarine for 15 minutes.
Add the two eggs, garlic powder, salt, pepper, parsley flakes, Parmesan cheese and enough bread crumbs to form stuffing consistency.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Blend in flour, seasonings and milk.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and place in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with additional cheese if desired.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine. Add soup and cheese, cooking and stirring until melted.
Add the broccoli and serve in chafing dish. Accompany with any cracker or sturdy chip.

title: eggplant with humous(chickpeas)
directions: Peel eggplant; cut in cubes and salt it.
Let dry for 2 hours, then fry in oil until brown.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil; add tomato, salt and pepper, then water and bring to boil for 10 minutes, then add humous.
Cook for 5 minutes, then add the fried eggplant.
Cook with low heat for 10 minutes until eggplant is done.
Pour in big dish.
Eat cold.
Makes enough for 4 people.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: oven rice dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients in casserole with cover.
Mix together and bake 45 minutes.
Stir and bake 30 minutes more.

title: poor man's pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven. Do not sift ingredients.
Do not grease pan.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into four dozen small meatballs.
Place in a shallow pan.
Brown in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve after heating in barbecue sauce.
Serve piping hot.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Saute pork or bacon slowly.
Remove and reserve scraps.
Add onions.
Stir and cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour until blended.
Stir in clam broth and add potatoes, tomatoes and green pepper.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are done.
Add pork (bacon) and clams and butter.
Simmer 5 more minutes.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Measure berries in a large pot.
Mix sugar in fruit and let set 10 minutes.
Mix water and pectin.
Pour over berries.
Stir well.
Pour in jars and seal.
Let stand at room temperature until set up (about 24 hours).
Put in freezer.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve 2 packages jello in boiling water.
Soften cream cheese with juice from pineapple.
Add pineapple, pecans and cream mixture to cooled jello mixture.
Fold in whipping cream; chill for several hours or overnight.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onions and parsley in a large bowl.
Mix Italian dressing, sugar and garlic; pour over salad and toss.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, at least 3 hours.

title: girl scout stew
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add all of remaining ingredients to the skillet and simmer slowly for 1/2 hour; stir often.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into tube pan. Bake at
250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Check;
it may take longer (it depends on oven).

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil; add peppers, onions and carrot strips. Cook until tender.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce.
Add to pan with pineapple and juice, vinegar and brown sugar.
Bring to a full boil.
Prepare rice.
Serve chicken over rice.
Serves 4.

title: catfish puppies
directions: Drain
liquid off catfish and mash well.
Add remaining ingredients
and
mix well.
May have to add liquid, such as 1 tablespoon	buttermilk
to make mixture easier to drop in oil. Have oil
very hot; fry until brown like hush puppies.
Always serve very	hot
with
your
choice
of
catsup, shrimp dip or tartar sauce.
Makes a large amount.

title: pork and mushroom dish
directions: Cut pork into 1/2-inch pieces (chunks).
Brown in oil.
You can roll pork in flour first if you want.
Add green beans and mushrooms and simmer on low for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk, egg yolks and sugar in top of double boiler.
Add flour and vanilla.
Cook, stirring until thickens.
Cut bananas. Line bowl with wafers and bananas; pour mixture over wafers and bananas.
Repeat 3 times.
Top with icing if desired.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, salt and 1 cup pecans.
Chill thoroughly.
Form into 1 large or 2 small balls. Coat with remaining pecans.
Chill.
Serve at room temperature with assorted crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat soup, Cheez Whiz and oleo until warm in saucepan. Add the rest of the ingredients and stir.
Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coconut surprise
directions: Mix.
Bake slowly 20 minutes at 325°.

title: tuna salad stack up
directions: Combine salad dressing, sour cream, pickles, onions, milk, and mustard.
Mix well.
Combine rice, peas, and parsley.
In a 3 1/2-quart salad bowl, layer lettuce, rice mixture, tomatoes, tuna and cucumbers.
Top with dressing.
Cover; chill.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Make the cheese sauce by melting the margarine.
Add the flour and blend.
Add milk and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add cooked broccoli, chicken and rice to the cheese sauce, stirring together. Spoon into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and walnuts; mix well.
Fold in egg whites. Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In shallow bowl, combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
In another shallow bowl, beat eggs and add milk.
In a third bowl combine parmesan and bread crumbs.
Coat chicken with flour mixtures, dip in egg mixture and roll in crumb mixture.
Place in a well greased 15 x 10 inch baking pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 400°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients in bowl until light and fluffy. Stir in mixture of flour and salt.
Chill, covered, for 1 hour. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into egg white.
Roll in pecans. Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Press with thumb.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes longer. Cookies will look doughy.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil several pieces of chicken, debone it and layer it in bottom of 13 x 10-inch casserole dish. Pour a can of cream of chicken soup over the chicken. Pour some of the broth that the chicken was boiled in over the soup. Mix up 1 1/2 cups of self-rising flour and 1 1/2 cups of milk and pour over the ingredients in the casserole dish. Sprinkle with black pepper. Save some of the broth back to pour over the pie as it begins to bake.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy tomato vinaigrette
directions: Arrange chicken in a shallow dish, add marinade, cover and refrigerate. Let stand for at least 2 hours (overnight is fine), turning once.

title: peach punch
directions: Mix fruit juices and chill; just before serving add ginger ale and garnish with cherries or mint sprigs. Serves 16.

title: karen's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken on High in microwave for 10 minutes.
Shred chicken.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with thick crust of crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: easy cookies
directions: Melt sugar in margarine.
Place crackers on a baking sheet (single layer).
Pour margarine and sugar over crackers and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
While still hot, top with 1 cup chocolate chips and nuts or sprinkles or colored sugar.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt milk and caramels over hot water.
After baking first mixture, sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Pour melted caramel mix over top.
Drop by spoonfuls rest of cake mix evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Note:
Make sure no unpopped kernels get into mixture.
Can be made into popcorn balls also.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: In electric skillet, combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Set heat at 280°.
Bring to boil and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until all ingredients are melted and blended.
Pour into 8 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Set aside.
Toss hot spaghetti with olive oil or butter.
Combine eggs and 1/2 cup fancy shredded Parmesan.
Stir into spaghetti.

title: banana loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Mix sugar, shortening and eggs. Beat until fluffy.
Add mashed bananas. Stir in sifted dry ingredients. Beat until smooth. Add nuts.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes. Wrap in foil when cool.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: clara's cranberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of hot water.
Add chilled cranberry sauce and stir.
Cool until firm, but not set.
Add nuts and fold in sour cream.
When folding in sour cream, do it as to have a marble effect.
Pour into mold.
Chill and serve.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and soup together.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Mix cracker crumbs, margarine and poppy seed. Place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (until hot and bubbly).

title: trifle
directions: In a large, deep clear bowl, line the bottom with chopped nuts.
Pour 3 jiggers of cordial over nuts.
Cut up angel food cake and fit all around in bowl.
Pour the fruit cocktail with juice all over cake, filling in holes.
Make jello, then pour on top of fruit and cake. Refrigerate 2 hours or until jello hardens. Make vanilla pudding or Birds custard and pour all over.
Add more nuts on top.
Before serving, cover with Cool Whip and decorate with cherries.

title: fruit dip(great with apple slices)
directions: Beat together until smooth and fluffy.
Serve with apples or other fruit.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Stir molasses and honey into the eggs.
Add oil to the egg mixture and beat into the dry ingredients.
Add green tomatoes and beat well.
Stir in the vanilla and chopped nuts.

title: chocolate plunge
directions: *Or use 2 (4 ounces each) packages Baker's German's sweet chocolate.

title: 6 layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce; sprinkle diced onion.
Spread bacon bits and peas.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Spread cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: crazy pumpkin pie
directions: Blend thoroughly.
Put in greased pie tin.
Put 1 teaspoon of cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Do not stir or mix.
Dump out of cans in exact order listed into ungreased 9 x 13-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angie's lump crab cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Spray cookie sheet 3 times with cooking spray.
Use bottom rack for baking.

title: lemon sauce(to be served with leftover cake)
directions: Put all together in pan on fire.
Stir constantly; pour boiling water in slowly still stirring until it becomes thick. Add juice of 1 lemon.

title: kenny's favorite enchiladas
directions: Combine cooked beef, 1 cup of sharp cheese and onion; set aside.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, tomato soup and enchilada sauce.
Set aside.
Warm tortillas.
Place 1 to 2 tablespoons of meat mixture on shell; roll up.
Place, seam side down, in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour sauce over the enchiladas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown peppers, onions and rice in butter.
Mix with consomme. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 375° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: hurricane cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake mix as directed in 2 round layer pans. Mix chocolate pudding as directed. Split cake in half.
Layer cake, then pudding, crushed Heath bars, and cool whip....continue and end with top layer of cool whip and candy.
Put in a large bowl.

title: never-fail pie dough
directions: Cut in shortening until like coarse cornmeal.

title: heavenly potatoes
directions: Day 1:
Cook potatoes, drain and refrigerate.

title: green beans au gratin
directions: Alternate layers of beans, soup, cheese and crumbs.
Spread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: wild western chili soup
directions: In large, heavy pan, brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 12 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil sugar and syrup (soft ball stage) until thready.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter until well mixed.
Pour over corn flakes; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: wine beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Combine all ingredients and cook until beans are done.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into two 9-inch shells.
Bake at 375° until set, about 45 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add flour, pecans and vanilla. Make into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets and roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool and roll in sugar again.
(I find a Ziploc bag works real well.)

title: summer squash casserole #2
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to instructions on box.
Place in 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole dish.
Slice squash in 1/4-inch slices and place on top of stuffing in wreath design. Heat soup with 1/3 cup water.
Pour over stuffing and squash. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
May garnish with chopped parsley or fresh tomatoes to serve.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces; brown in oil.
While browning, add salt and pepper to taste.
Set chicken aside after all browned.
In same skillet, add soup, milk, paprika and red pepper.
Cook until heated; add chicken.
Cook until heated through and chicken is fully cooked.
Add sour cream.
Cook until heated thoroughly.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: sugar-free cherry pie
directions: Heat juice for Jell-O and other ingredients and cook until thick. Pour over cherries in pie crust. Add top crust. Be sure to poke several holes in top crust. Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then at 350° until done.

title: lazy woman's cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, milk and eggs thoroughly.
Pour over oleo.
Place drained peaches on top of batter. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Take from oven and dab with butter and brown sugar.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: Prepare
the
cake
mix according to directions.
Spoon the batter into
the cones until they are 2/3 full.
Place the cones in
the
muffin
pan
and
bake according to the package directions.
When the cakes are cool, frost and decorate them.

title: cucumber slices in sour cream
directions: Sprinkle sliced cucumber with salt; let stand about 30 minutes. Drain thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers.
Chill about 30 minutes before serving.
Heap in lettuce cups; sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove bone and skin from salmon.
Mix all together and form into a loaf.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in lightly greased pan.

title: fried corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Cut corn from cobs and cook in bacon drippings for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add enough milk to make a creamy consistency.
Add butter and cook another 5 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together. Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top. Dabble butter on top of crackers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: Feel free to use instant potatoes in this recipe, no one will know.

title: wassail pot
directions: Put sugar, molasses, cider and juices in cooker.
Add 2 cups hot water.
Add spices; stir to blend.
Cook on low for 5 hours. Add liquor (optional) 15 minutes before serving.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients together
and
put
in	pie shell.
Dot with 1 1/2 tablespoons
butter.
Cover
with top crust.
Brush top crust with milk.	Bake at 425° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: jan's famous hot sauce
directions: Optional:
Use spiced tomatoes instead of regular tomatoes.

title: vegetarian lasagna(microwave)
directions: Place packages of spinach in a 2-quart glass dish.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Drain out all moisture; set aside.
Crumble tofu into bowl; stir in cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese; set aside.
Combine spaghetti sauce, wine, garlic powder and nutmeg in a glass bowl.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Remove and set aside 1 cup of sauce.
Add spinach to sauce remaining in bowl.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend together apricots and coconut. Stir in condensed milk.
Shape into small balls and roll in sugar. Let stand in air until firm.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: apple goodie
directions: Peel and slice apples (heaping) into an 8 x 8 pan.
Add sugar, flour and cinnamon.

title: cold carrot pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salt water until fork-tender.
When cool, alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion rings.

title: salted peanut crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend together flour, salt and soda; stir in.
Mix in peanuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of greased glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: quick sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute green pepper and onions.
Add soup.
Bring to a slow boil.
Add sour cream.
Stir and remove from heat.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer tortillas, cut up chicken and sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with cheese mix and jalapenos.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: In small bowl, combine butter, vanilla, corn syrup and salt. Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Divide in half and roll into logs.
Wrap in plastic.
Place quarter piece in palm of hand to flatten.
Evenly wrap around cherry to cover.
Place on wax lined cookie sheets and freeze 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth.
Dip cherries into chocolate and shake off excess.
Place on wax lined cookie sheets.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Serve immediately or store in refrigerator.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Saute turkey and onion.
Spread Ricotta cheese evenly over turkey.
Put noodles over Ricotta cheese.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken breast and stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: banana nut bread(fun and easy for children to make)
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter and egg.
Add flour and vanilla flavor.
Mash and add bananas, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Add 1 cup water and 1 cup blueberries (fresh or frozen) and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix well.
Add 3 cups uncooked blueberries and mix well.
Pour into a baked and cooled pie crust. Chill and keep in refrigerator.

title: bavarian banana delight(serves 15 to 20)
directions: Top with sliced bananas and crushed pineapple.
Cover with large carton whipped topping.
Sprinkle with nuts and chopped maraschino cherries, if desired.
Refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: chicken baste
directions: Mix and baste chicken.
Cook real slow for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: choco-berry frozen dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan with foil.
In a large mixer bowl, beat 2 packages cream cheese.
Blend in syrup and water; beat until smooth.
Fold in 3 cups whipped topping.
Spoon half of chocolate mixture into prepared pan.
Freeze for 15 minutes. Chill remaining chocolate mixture.
In a small mixer bowl, beat remaining package of cream cheese.
Blend in strawberries until smooth.
Fold in remaining 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Spoon strawberry mixture over chocolate layer in pan.
Top with chilled chocolate mixture.
Cover.
Freeze several hours or overnight until firm.
Unmold about 10 minutes before serving.
Peel off foil before slicing.

title: sugar cookie cutouts
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together until light and fluffy. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Beat well. Chill dough 1 hour. Roll dough 1/8-inch thick. Cut into desired shapes. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets 6 to 8 minutes at 400°. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions.
Brown beef and drain; then add seasonings.
Mix well.
Put 1/2 of mixture in large casserole dish.
Top with 8 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Layer with 1/2 of pepperoni.
Add remaining mixture and layer again with rest of cheese and pepperoni.
If desired, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Uncover and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: hot brats
