directions: Brown bratwursts in oil and drain.
Add beer and simmer for 20 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, mustard, horseradish sauce and vinegar.
Add mixture to beer and brats.
Cook until bubbly.
Keep warm in crock-pot until ready to serve.

title: quick apple pies
directions: Roll biscuits out thin.
Put chopped apples on biscuits.
Fold over, crease and seal edges with a fork.
Boil sugar, Mellow Yellow, butter and cinnamon.
Boil until sugar dissolves.
Pour over pies (in baking dish).
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 375° in a loaf pan for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir sherbet into jello until melted.
Add marshmallows.
Allow mixture to cool, then stir fruit into mixture!
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into individual molds and freeze.

title: jeanne's vegetable soup
directions: In a large soup pot, combine the broth, water, seasoning, carrots, onions, celery and potatoes. Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are barely cooked.
Add the stewed tomatoes and cabbage and simmer until cabbage is cooked.

title: handy hot dish
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Stir several times during baking.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
This will keep refrigerated 10 days.
Bake in muffin tins in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes as needed.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco in flour.
Add milk and mix real well.
Roll out in saucer size dough.
Add pie filling.
Moisten around edge, press together with fork.
Fry in pan of hot oil.

title: creamy fettuccini alfredo
directions: In large pan combine cream cheese, parmesan cheese, margarine and milk.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add pasta and toss lightly.
You can add broccoli, chicken and/or shrimp.

title: collard greens with neck bones
directions: Parboil neck bones in large saucepan.
Remove from broth.
Add greens.
Cook on low heat until tender.
Add bacon drippings and red pepper sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until it thickens.
Stir every 15 minutes while baking.

title: best ever corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Mix dry ingredients. Slightly beat egg, oleo and evaporated milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt chocolate pieces over hot water; cool slightly.
Mix with eggs.
Fold in whipping cream, vanilla and nuts.
Tear angel food cake in small pieces.
Line oblong cake pan 13 x 9 1/2 x 2 with half of cake pieces.
Pour half of filling over cake.
Add more cake pieces and more filling.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Chill several hours.
Cut in squares.

title: veggie spaghetti
directions: Chop all veggies and steam in microwave steamer.
Add spaghetti mix and favorite seasonings.
Cook spaghetti until tender. Combine and stir in tomato sauce.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: This cake is prepared in three steps.
Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, mix together cake mix, melted butter, 2 eggs and 1 cup of nuts.
Spread mixture in 9 x 9-inch square cake pan.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Place the molasses, sugar, ginger, and cinnamon in a saucepan over medium heat.
Stir constantly until sugar has melted.
Add baking soda and stir.
When the mixture bubbles up, remove from heat.

title: angel dessert
directions: Bread angel food cake into 1/2 to 1-inch cubes.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip to milk and cream cheese mixture.
Fold cake into mixture and spread in 13 x 9-inch dish or pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over top of cake mixture.
Refrigerate for one hour and serve in 1 1/2-inch square portions.

title: venison corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; add celery and onion.
Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Reduce heat; stir in soup, corn, beans and seasonings.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Top with corn chips and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until chips are slightly toasted.

title: shrimp enchiladas
directions: Melt butter in a 3 quart saucepan.
Saute onions until tender. Add shrimp and cook until shrimp turns pink.
Add green chilies. Add soups, cream cheese and creole seasonings.
Heat over medium heat until cream cheese melts and blends in.
Put 1/3 cup mixture in center of each tortilla and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place seam side down in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour any remaining filling mixture over enchiladas.
Spread evenly.
Top with shredded cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 10 enchiladas.

title: banana boats
directions: Use bananas that are firm and not overripe.
Peel back one section of banana skin.
Make one slit the length of the banana. Fill with 4 or 5 chocolate chips and 4 or 5 mini marshmallows. Press then down slightly into the slit.
Replace skin to cover the opening.
Place on grill over coals for about 10 minutes.
Eat with spoon out of skin.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and beat with beater until creamy. Let stand overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Roll into logs or balls.
Roll in parsley or chopped nuts.
Makes 2 logs or balls.

title: nut roll
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter on low heat.
Crush crackers; cut up pecans and cherries.
Mix all together with melted marshmallows.
Put on waxed paper and make into a roll.
Will keep in freezer or refrigerator a long time.
When ready to use, slice and serve.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix well flour, sugar, butter and chopped nuts and press into a dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool and spread the following mixtures over crust:

title: young folks punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar together.
Add juices, water and ginger ale.
Serve with ice.

title: crock-pot chili beans
directions: Cook ground beef and drain off grease.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot.
This can be done in the morning before going to work. Cook on low and chili will be ready for dinner.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream in a mixing bowl. Add salmon and mix until well blended.

title: rosemary jelly
directions: Pour boiling apple juice over rosemary and let stand 20 minutes.
Strain into saucepan.
Add lemon juice and enough fruit juice to make two cups.
Add sugar.
Bring to boil, and stir in pectin.
Boil hard for one minute.
Pour into sterilized glasses. A few rosemary leaves may be placed on top before sealing.

title: spaghetti fruit salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 4 minutes. Set aside to cool completely. Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water. Place in a large bowl. Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Pour the juice over the spaghetti; toss in the apples and toss gently. Stir in egg mixture and pineapple. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Fold in whipped topping just before serving. Garnish with walnuts and cherries. Yield:
12 to 14 servings.

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: Cut rind into pieces and add to juice and put in covered pitcher with 3 ounces of sugar.
Pour in 1 quart water brought to boiling point.
Let stand until cooled.
Chill in refrigerator. Pour into pitcher in which thin slices of orange and bits of pineapple have been added.
Decorate with cherries.
One quart equals 10 drinks.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drain in colander. Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° about 25 or 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put bacon on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: zucchini-streusel bundt cake
directions: Place zucchini on several layers of paper towels; cover with additional paper towels.
Let stand 5 minutes, pressing down occasionally.
Set aside.

title: leslie's taco soup
directions: Cook meat and onions until meat is no longer pink.
Mix all ingredients together. Cook until warm.
Serve over Fritos.
Serve with cheese and sour cream.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on large pizza pan, about 15-inches diameter, up to top edge.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine bacon, potatoes and onion.
Add salt, pepper, dry mustard, sugar, water, vinegar and egg to bacon drippings.
Cook mixture until egg thickens.
Pour over bacon-onion-potato mixture and heat until liquid is absorbed.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cook together pineapple, flour and sugar until thick; cool. Add sliced bananas, coconut and nuts to cooled mixture.
Stir well and pour into 2 cooked pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in double boiler and melt over low heat.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Pour in pie shell and chill.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: apple rice salad
directions: Mix all together.
Add dressing and season to taste.

title: old-fashioned raisin cake
directions: Bring raisins and water to boil; mash some with potato masher. Add soda and stir. Let stand while you mix the following: shortening and sugar. Second, mix eggs, flavoring, flour, baking powder and salt. Add raisins to first mixture and stir, then add 2nd mixture and stir in. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with sugar (1/2 cup). Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: martha's nut roll* * * * *
directions: Martha's Nut Roll is a Georgia recipe.
The nuts should be very fine, but not like flour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put 1/2 cup cracker crumbs on top.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Remove from heat; save broth. Pull chicken from bone. Put back in broth as you pull off bone. Add spices. Cut biscuits into quarters. Drop in broth. Mix flour and water and bring broth to boil.
Add flour mixture to broth. Cook until biscuits are done.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut breast meat into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
In cup, mix vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce, water and salt.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook onion until tender.
Increase heat to medium high; add chicken.
Cook, stirring until chicken is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add frozen peas, pineapple chunks with juice and cornstarch mixture.
Cook, stirring frequently until mixture boils and thickens.

title: cream puff
directions: Boil water and butter.
Remove from heat; add flour to mixture with fork.
Add eggs, one at a time, then spread on cookie sheet. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: grandma townsley's split pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Drain and add fresh water.
Add all other ingredients and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add water, if necessary.
Soup will be thick and creamy.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: peaches and cream cheese pie
directions: Combine; sprinkle over cream cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until crust is golden.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Also tastes great warm.

title: jello party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add cold water and sugar.
Keep in liquid form.
Add the juices.
When ready to serve, add the ginger ale.

title: spicy baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain. Add Manwich. Combine with baked beans in slow cooker.
Makes about 12-15 servings.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; spread on bottom of dish. Drain chili sauce over cheese spread.
Drain crab meat and spread over chili sauce.
Sprinkle parsley over crab meat.
Make up 1 day ahead, wrap with waxed paper and then foil.
Keep in refrigerator until 1 hour prior to serving.

title: cheese christmas tree
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in blender or food processor until well mixed.
Shape over funnel to form tree.
Garnish with parsley and pimentos.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple in bottom of a baking dish that has been greased. Pour cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Dump cake mix.
Put margarine in slices on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Take out; sprinkle top with nuts and put back in oven for 15 minutes.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In large pan, blend in first 5 ingredients.
Stir in water; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour in a little juice (syrup) in quart jar 1/2-inch.
Pack apples into jars and fill with syrup, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Put lids on and process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes for quart jars.
Yields 7 to 8 quarts.

title: shrimp paella
directions: In 2 1/2-quart casserole, cook onion, garlic and olive oil. Stir in tomatoes, clam juice, rice, saffron or turmeric, salt and pepper.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Cook until rice is tender. Peel and devein shrimp.
Stir into rice with peas.
Cook until shrimp turns pink.
Cut pimento into strips and slice olives. Stir into shrimp.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add ingredients to cooked broccoli mix, sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix hamburger into meatballs.
Roll in flour and brown.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and pour over the meatballs. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Pour over rice (optional).

title: outstanding breakfast
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.
Cube bread.
Layer bacon, cheese and bread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk and spices. Pour over layered ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight (at least 4 hours).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: s'mores(child's recipe)
directions: Take a graham cracker.
Add 6 milk chocolate squares.
Top it with a marshmallow.
Microwave on High for 10 to 15 seconds.
Top it with second graham cracker and enjoy.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Layer pineapple mixture. Top with crackers, then melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn confection
directions: Combine brown sugar, syrup, margarine and cream of tartar in saucepan.
Bring to a hard rolling boil, stirring until sugar is melted, boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda.
Pour over popcorn; mix well.
Place in roaster pan.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for about 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container.
Peanuts may be added if desired.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Alternate dry ingredients and pumpkin to creamed mixture.
Blend well, stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake large loaves at 350° for 65 minutes, small loaves at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate wafer and graham cracker brownies
directions: In a bowl whisk together 2 eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons water, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla until the mixture is smooth and stir in the chocolate wafer crumbs, chocolate chips and half the butter.

In another bowl whisk together the remaining 2 eggs, brown sugar, 2 tablespoons water, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until smooth and stir in the graham cracker crumbs, pecans and remaining butter.	Drop large spoonfuls of each mixture alternately into greased 8-inch square baking pan.	Run a knife blade through the mixtures to marble the batter and smooth the top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: cottage pie
directions: Heat a nonstick pan; chop the bacon and put into the pan. When the fat runs out of the bacon, add the meat and allow to brown, turning the mixture frequently.
Slice the onion thinly, add to the meat and cook for a few minutes until soft.
Slice the tomato and mushrooms.
Add these to the pan and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add seasoning to taste.
Sprinkle the flour into the pan.
Continue to stir whilst adding the beef stock.
When the mixture has thickened, simmer gently for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast sweet bread
directions: Blend Bisquick mix and sugar together.
Combine eggs and water or milk and stir into mix.
Add raisins.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top, adding nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Best served hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix cheese, Worcestershire sauce, enhancer and chopped green onions.
Shape into a ball.
Tear the dried beef into small pieces and cover the cheese ball with them.
Wrap ball in foil and refrigerate.
Let stand at least 6 hours before serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and add flour and baking powder to mixture.
Fold in egg whites; roll out, quarter inch. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Mix with butter and milk.
Pour into pan.
Put fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Mix until smooth.
When both of the above are done, stir 1/8 teaspoon soda in the tomato soup mixture and after it has foamed up and settled, pour the medium white sauce into the tomato soup and serve.
Do not boil anymore.
Serve with hot cornbread!

title: joyce thomas' hot crab fondue
directions: Mix all together very well except crabmeat and 1/4 of the cheese.
Layer 1/3 of the filling, 1/2 of the crabmeat (trying not to break the lumps), 1/3 of the filling, 1/2 of the crabmeat, ending with the final 1/3 of the filling.
Sprinkle on the reserved cheese and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh italian sausage and sauce
directions: Brown sausage in olive oil about 10 minutes, turning frequently.
Remove sausage and set aside.
Saute onions lightly for 2 to 3 minutes in same pot.
Add garlic and rest of ingredients to pot.
Stir to blend.
Return sausage to pot.
Simmer at least 45 minutes.
Serve with your favorite pasta!
Delicioso!

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar. Cut in the butter until very fine crumbs.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Beat eggs, granulated sugar and lemon juice.
Sift in the 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for another 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool and cut.

title: sharon's chicken
directions: Clean and dry chicken, place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and spices. Pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Top with bread crumbs.
Pour 1/2 of butter over chicken.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain thoroughly.
Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add salt, pepper, and flour gradually.
Add enough flour to make stiff enough to roll.
Roll into long roll and chill.
Slice and bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Put half of stuffing in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of stuffing.
Mix soup, milk, broth and onion together.
Then pour soup mixture on top of chicken.
Place other half of stuffing on top.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sunflower cheese crisps
directions: Cut butter into flour and salt to resemble fine crumbs.
Beat in cottage cheese until smooth. Stir in seeds.
Roll half of dough into a 12 x 16-inch rectangle 1/16-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Prick squares.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together in the order given.
Pour into lightly greased and floured oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in 375° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: autumn soup
directions: In Dutch oven or 3-quart stock pot, brown meat; drain.	Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Very good!

title: baked beans
directions: Cut pineapple in half and drain.
Saute onion and peppers. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes or can be baked in 350° oven.

title: spiced meatballs and sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter, in a large mixing bowl. Mix well and shape into one-inch balls.
Saute meatballs in butter until browned.
Drain well and set aside.
Prepare sauce.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in deep pie pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: braised cornish hens
directions: Split hens in half lengthwise and place in single layer in a shallow baking dish.
Gently loosen skin from meat on breast of each half to form a pocket.
Pour chicken broth over.
Whip butter in small bowl with fork until fluffy.
Stir in wine, green onions, tarragon, parsley, garlic salt and pepper, mixing well.
Place rounded tablespoonful of the butter mixture in the pocket of each half breast.
Braise, covered, in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour, basting with drippings every 15 minutes.
Hens are done when tender and juices run clear when thigh is pierced with a fork.
Serve hot.

title: brazilian rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir into rice.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart baking dish and bake in a pan of water in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Can be made 24 hours ahead.

title: marshmallow fudge cake
directions: Put butter and cocoa in boiler.
Melt.
Mix other ingredients in mixing bowl. When butter and cocoa are melted, pour over the other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased pan.
Cook about 20 minutes at 375°.
Take from oven, turn over and place marshmallows on top of warm cake.
When cake is cool, ice with confectioners sugar icing.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Prepare Potato Buds according to package directions, using water, milk, 2 to 3 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon salt. Add cream cheese, sour cream, soup, 1/2 teaspoon salt, onion salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons butter. Place in buttered baking dish. At this point, potatoes can be refrigerated several days or frozen until needed. Thaw frozen potatoes in microwave or refrigerator.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add oil and continue to beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add pumpkin.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cheese squash crisp
directions: Arrange squash in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan so squash are no more than 1 to 1 1/2 inches thick in pan.
Mix water and lemon juice.
Pour over squash.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Make topping by combining sugar, flour, salt and margarine.
Work with fork to form a crumbly mixture.
Mix in grated cheese.
Cover top of squash with topping and press down hard.
Bake at 350° (325° glass pan) for 45 minutes or until light brown.
Broil for 5 to 10 minutes to brown top for crispness, careful not to burn.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Arrange chilled shrimp in 4 lettuce-lined sherbet dishes. Spoon some cocktail sauce atop each serving. Garnish each with lemon wedges. Makes 4 servings.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Using a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer ingredients; celery, eggs, peas, green peppers, onions and bacon.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread on the top like frosting.
Top with grated cheese. Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours.

title: gramma swearinger's noodles
directions: Combine egg, salt and milk; add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll very thin on floured surface and let stand for 20 minutes.
Roll up and slice 1/8-inch thick; spread out the noodles and let dry for 2 hours.
Drop into boiling soup, broth or salted water.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: corn sausage soup
directions: Break up sausage and cook until brown.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add potatoes, onions, green pepper and water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in corn.
Add milk to flour until well blended.
Add to soup.
Stir in salt, pepper and parsley.
Cook until thickened.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth, about 2 minutes on high with hand mixer.
Pour into pie plate, bake at 325 F 50-55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and Jell-O over low heat until Jell-O melts. Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: orange blossom muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and stir vigorously. Stir in marmalade and nuts. Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.

title: spinach squares
directions: Thaw spinach; drain well.
Melt butter.
Sift flour and baking powder into butter.
Stir well.
Add spinach and diced Brick cheese.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Beat eggs well and stir into spinach mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sour potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Add mustard, butter and pepper. Let simmer for 5 minutes.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, white corn syrup, butter and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, over medium heat, until it reaches soft ball stage on candy thermometer or until a little dropped in cold water makes a soft ball.
Remove from heat and let stand for 15 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: jessie cloud's prize winning chili
directions: Saute onions
in
melted
shortening
until they change color. Add chili meat and cook until pink is gone.
Drain off fat (this is	the
secret to preventing heartburn).
Add chili powder, cumin, salt,
red
pepper,	paprika
and tomato juice. Simmer 40 minutes.
Add
enough
quick-cooking oats to thicken to taste.

title: flag cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan. After baking, cool for 15 minutes.

title: calico chicken casserole
directions: Cook package of medium noodles and then drain.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Cut beef into small pieces and brown in oil.
Add onion and cut-up mushrooms.
When mushrooms are soft, add soup, water and wine.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or more, stirring every 15 minutes. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: pear upside-down cake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in an 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter.
Pare and core pears; slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange on top of brown sugar.
Place a cherry in center of each slice.
Cream butter.
Add 1/2 cup granulated sugar. Cream well.
Add egg; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Mix the sifted flour, baking powder and salt; add to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Pour batter over pears.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and green pepper.
Add soup, tomato and chicken; heat.
When hot, at last minute add cream cheese and sour cream.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: grandma's apple-lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and a few drops of lemon juice.
Beat until stiff; spread on pie and bake until brown.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Scoop by teaspoon and roll into balls; dip in sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: garden supper casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix bread cubes, cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Spread 1/2 the mixture in greased 1-quart casserole; top with vegetables.
Cook and stir onion in 3 tablespoons of butter until onion is tender.
Blend in flour and seasoning.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in meat.
Pour over vegetables. Arrange tomato slices on top; sprinkle with remaining bread mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into ball. Refrigerate.

title: volcano cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Do not flour.

title: skillet new potatoes
directions: Thinly slice the potatoes.
Chop onions.
Melt margarine in skillet, then add mixture of potatoes and onions several layers deep and cover.
They can be turned occasionally and slightly browned but basically are cooled by steam.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Beat together the soft oleomargarine, sugar and egg.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt.
Mix these ingredients alternately with the milk.
Fill 2/3 full in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan at once while still hot; roll in sugar or sugar and cinnamon. Makes 1 dozen.

title: winter tomato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Toss lightly. Add enough coarsely broken crackers to absorb the liquid.

title: sausage and corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle a little catsup on top.
If grease comes to the top while cooking, spoon off.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Stew chicken with water, salt, pepper, onion and celery leaves.
When
done,
remove
meat from bones, cut into pieces and return
to broth.
Add corn, parsley and noodles.
Boil 15 minutes all of ingredients.
Add chopped, hard-cooked eggs.

title: filling for cake
directions: Mix and cook slowly in heavy pan until thick all ingredients except pecans and vanilla.
Add the pecans and vanilla.
Cool and spread between layers and on top.
Halve recipe for one-layer skillet cake.

title: peach and cream cheese pie
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, pudding, egg and milk together.
Pour into a greased 9-inch cake pan or 10-inch pie pan.
Place on top, one layer of drained peach halves.
Next mix the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Spread over peaches about 1-inch away from edge of pan.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homemade play dough(this is not to eat; it's play dough!)
directions: Heat water, salt, oil and food coloring to boiling.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients.
Knead until smooth.
Mixture will be hot at first; consider using rubber gloves.
Store in airtight container; will stay pliable for months (6 weeks during summer).

title: philly fudge
directions: Cream cheese until soft.
Blend in sugar slowly.
Melt chocolate, cool slightly and add to cheese mixture.
Add vanilla, salt and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Press into greased pan. Place in refrigerator until firm, about 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Layer beans, sour cream and salsa in square shallow dish and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese and heat until melted.
Serve with Doritos or Fritos.

title: hot wassail
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes the first 4 ingredients.
Add apple cider, hot water, pineapple, orange juice, red hot candy and orange slice.
May put in a crock-pot to keep hot enough to serve.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Saute chicken pieces in butter in large frypan.
Remove when lightly browned.
Add onions, flour, paprika, salt and pepper and stir.
Add chicken broth; stir and cook until smooth.
Stir in sour cream and Worcestershire.
Mix half the sauce with cooked noodles and pour into 3-quart casserole.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of noodles.
Pour rest of sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: honey berry lemonade
directions: Squeeze the lemons and stir in the honey gradually.
Taste to see if it is the right sweetness.
When the honey and lemon juice are thoroughly combined, add the water and the berries in a pitcher.
Pour into glasses that have been frosted in the freezer and are half full of ice.
Decorate each glass with a sprig of mint.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bake in square or oblong pan.
May be iced, but good without.

title: pineapple over chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in flat roast pan.
Drain juice from pineapple and pour over chicken.
Dot chicken with butter and spread onion over top.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade bologna
directions: Mix with hand; roll into 2 rolls.
Wrap rolls in Saran Wrap. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in shallow pan at 300°. Turn 1 time to brown evenly.
Cool on rack.

title: california casserole
directions: Mix
all
these
ingredients together except butter and crackers.
Put
in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Use 1 (one)
stack Ritz crackers and mix with 1/2 cup melted butter. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix following directions on package using the oil, eggs and juice drained from oranges.
Mix well.
Fold in oranges and nuts.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool for 10 minutes then frost.

title: nanny's old fashion biscuits
directions: Mix all except milk.
Crumble.
Gradually add milk, enough to moisten.
Mold into 8 rounds and bake in a greased round cake tin at 425° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix and bring the first

four ingredients to a boil. Let cool to room temperature. Chop fresh ingredients and add all canned goods in large plastic container. Add liquid mixture to chopped ingredients. Mix and store in fridge. Serve with Frito scoops or serve as a side salad. Will store in refrigerator in canning jar up to two weeks.

title: baked salmon
directions: Open can; drain off stock and save it for use for basting. Remove all bones and skim from salmon.
Cut onion and green pepper in small pieces.
Beat eggs and all ingredients and mix well. Pour in baking dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes. Uncover and brown.
Remove from oven and pour the drained stock over the salmon.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: weight watcher's cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup of the water over low heat.
Put into blender.
Add rest of the ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and refrigerate until set.
Cut pie into 4 pieces.
Counts as 1 fruit and 1 milk.
